00:50.567 --> 00:54.570
MAN 1 [ON RADIO]:
- Clearly, I've never been there, but...

00:56.573 --> 01:00.659
MAN 2:usually the situation,
obviously a major malfunction.

01:00.827 --> 01:03.579
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGES ON RADIO]

01:14.883 --> 01:17.134
MAN 3:
- Whether or not their president is a crook.

01:17.302 --> 01:18.594
MAN 4:
Well, I'm not a crook.

01:18.761 --> 01:22.597
MAN 5:
- Small step for man, one giant leap for...

01:22.764 --> 01:26.934
MAN 6: Robert Kennedy was shot
in that ballroom.

01:28.437 --> 01:31.105
MAN 7:
Thank God almighty, we are free at last.

01:31.273 --> 01:33.900
MAN 8:
A sniper has fired at President Kennedy.

01:41.283 --> 01:42.617
MAN 9:
- The Communist party...

01:42.784 --> 01:45.036
...or have you ever been
a member of the Communist party?

01:45.204 --> 01:49.457
MAN 10:
Old soldiers never die. They just...

01:49.625 --> 01:52.210
MAN 11:
Hi-yo, Silver!

01:53.879 --> 01:56.714
MAN 12:
- Something never before experienced...

01:56.882 --> 02:01.302
MAN 13:
- 1941, a date which will live...

02:05.641 --> 02:10.019
MAN 14: And we continue this final edition
of our Maxwell House Good News of 1939.

02:10.187 --> 02:12.313
MAN 15: Good evening,
Mr. And Mrs. North America...

02:12.481 --> 02:14.857
...and all the ships at sea.
Let's go to press.

02:19.071 --> 02:23.491
[MUSIC AND CHATTER FADING]

03:32.393 --> 03:36.563
GIRL:
CQ, this is W-9 GFO.

03:38.065 --> 03:42.527
CQ, this is W-9 GFO here. Come back?

03:44.113 --> 03:45.530
CQ.

03:45.698 --> 03:50.201
CQ, this is W-9 GFO here.

03:50.369 --> 03:52.037
Come back?

03:52.580 --> 03:54.039
[KNOCKING]

03:54.206 --> 03:55.373
[DOOR OPENS]

03:55.541 --> 04:00.545
CQ, CQ, this is W-9 GFO.
Is anybody out there?

04:00.713 --> 04:02.005
Not getting anything.

04:02.173 --> 04:03.757
Small moves, Ellie.

04:05.217 --> 04:06.593
Small moves.

04:09.095 --> 04:13.599
CQ, this is W-9 GFO here. Come back?

04:13.767 --> 04:17.769
MAN:
Copy, W-9 GFO. K-4 WLD here.

04:17.937 --> 04:21.190
- What do I say?
- Just be yourself.

04:21.649 --> 04:25.861
- Where are you, K-4 WLD? Come back?
- Pensacola. Over.

04:26.029 --> 04:27.613
Pensacola, where's Pensacola?

04:27.781 --> 04:29.782
I'll give you a hint.

04:29.949 --> 04:31.241
Orange juice.

04:33.953 --> 04:37.790
Copy that, K-4 WLD.
How's the weather down there in Florida?

04:39.084 --> 04:41.335
TED:
Pensacola, Florida.

04:41.503 --> 04:44.171
I have to tell you, Sparks...

04:44.339 --> 04:47.841
...one thousand, one hundred
and sixteen miles.

04:48.009 --> 04:51.470
Pretty good. That's the farthest yet.

05:03.858 --> 05:07.152
ELLIE: Can we hear all the way to New York?
TED: Sure.

05:08.530 --> 05:12.491
ELLIE: Can we hear all the way to California?
TED: I don't see why not.

05:13.243 --> 05:16.954
ELLIE: Can we hear all the way to Alaska?
TED: Yeah, on a really clear day.

05:17.163 --> 05:19.665
ELLIE:
Can we hear all the way to China?

05:20.208 --> 05:22.251
TED:
On a really, really clear day.

05:22.419 --> 05:23.836
[CHUCKLING]

05:24.546 --> 05:27.172
ELLIE:
Could we talk to the moon?

05:27.340 --> 05:30.175
TED: Well, if it's a big enough radio,
I don't see why not.

05:30.843 --> 05:32.844
ELLIE:
Could we talk to Jupiter?

05:33.053 --> 05:35.847
Or what's the one after that?

05:36.014 --> 05:37.849
Don't tell me.

05:39.685 --> 05:41.352
TED:
I'll give you a hint.

05:41.520 --> 05:42.687
Hula-Hoops.

05:42.896 --> 05:46.190
- Saturn. Could we talk to Saturn?
- Mm-hm.

05:50.779 --> 05:53.781
Dad, could we talk to Mom?

05:58.871 --> 06:01.956
I don't think even the biggest radio
could reach that far.

06:07.087 --> 06:09.380
All right, no more stalling.

06:10.924 --> 06:12.383
Okay.

06:13.969 --> 06:15.344
Pensacola.

06:22.144 --> 06:24.479
Oh, Ellie, that's a beauty.

06:25.981 --> 06:27.732
Now get some sleep.

06:35.741 --> 06:37.783
- Hey, Dad?
- Yeah?

06:37.951 --> 06:40.745
Do you think there's people
on other planets?

06:40.913 --> 06:42.580
I don't know, Sparks.

06:44.082 --> 06:46.083
But I guess I'd say...

06:46.251 --> 06:48.419
...if it is just us...

06:49.588 --> 06:51.923
...it seems like an awful waste of space.

07:08.940 --> 07:11.274
CQ, CQ.

07:11.442 --> 07:13.777
CQ, this is W-9 GFO.

07:13.986 --> 07:17.113
Repeat. This is W-9 GFO. Come back?

07:18.658 --> 07:22.035
CQ, this is W-9 GFO. Come back?

07:24.664 --> 07:27.123
I'm gonna need a bigger antenna.

07:53.693 --> 07:55.443
MAN:
What do you think, Doctor Arroway?

07:55.611 --> 07:57.612
Isn't she a beauty?

08:01.158 --> 08:02.284
It'll do.

08:02.493 --> 08:04.452
FISHER:
The village is five miles away.

08:04.662 --> 08:09.249
There's a general store in the cantina.
They can order anything from San Juan.

08:09.417 --> 08:11.001
ELLIE:
And when can I get some dish time?

08:11.168 --> 08:14.546
FISHER: Dr. Clark said you wouldn't
be able to wait. Your first shift is tonight.

08:14.714 --> 08:15.839
ELLIE:
All right.

09:01.051 --> 09:03.385
[STATIC BUZZING OVER RADIO]

09:10.977 --> 09:12.478
Go back.

09:13.897 --> 09:16.982
Try back a little bit.
You had something there.

09:17.150 --> 09:18.192
[WHIRRING ON RADIO]

09:18.360 --> 09:19.443
There.

09:19.611 --> 09:22.696
- Right there?
- You hear it? Right there, that's it.

09:22.864 --> 09:26.742
ELLIE: All right, 1221.46.
That's well within the L band.

09:26.910 --> 09:29.995
- Check off-axis.
- Uh-huh. On it.

09:31.081 --> 09:33.749
It's not in the neighborhood.

09:39.381 --> 09:41.048
Ah.

09:42.216 --> 09:46.094
Here it is. J-1741 plus 2748.

09:46.261 --> 09:49.931
Catalogued November 4, 1982. Pulsar.

09:50.766 --> 09:55.269
Well, I don't know, it must've been...
The glitch in the timing is what threw me.

09:55.437 --> 09:57.146
Must've been a starquake.

09:57.314 --> 09:58.356
[WHIRRING STOPS]

09:58.524 --> 10:02.360
I think it's great that you listen.
Most people don't do that anymore.

10:02.528 --> 10:05.405
It's just an old habit.
You know, it makes it feel more real.

10:05.572 --> 10:08.449
- Ellie.
- Kent. Kent Clark.

10:09.493 --> 10:10.618
Hey.

10:10.786 --> 10:15.081
They said you've been up at Owens Valley
working under Drumlin.

10:15.249 --> 10:16.833
How did you like him?

10:17.000 --> 10:18.292
[ELLIE SIGHS]

10:19.795 --> 10:24.132
That much? And about what I'd expect
after what he had to say about you.

10:24.299 --> 10:26.300
What was that?

10:26.468 --> 10:29.595
That you are brilliant, driven...

10:29.763 --> 10:32.765
...a major pain in the ass,
and obsessed with a field of study...

10:32.933 --> 10:36.102
...that he considers tantamount
to professional suicide.

10:37.020 --> 10:40.148
- Anything else?
- Those were the highlights.

10:40.315 --> 10:42.608
Davio, Dr. Vernon. Dr. Arroway.

10:42.776 --> 10:44.235
ELLIE: Hey. Hi there.
- How you doing?

10:44.403 --> 10:48.990
And I believe you've already met our
tireless research assistant, Mr. Fisher...

10:49.158 --> 10:51.951
- Here, I need you to sign...
...as well as his cologne.

10:52.119 --> 10:54.704
Brook's looking at the black hole
at the center of M-87.

10:54.872 --> 10:58.624
Eli's studying Markarian 541,
a major gamma-ray source.

10:58.792 --> 11:03.838
And Dr. Arroway will be spending her
precious telescope time listening for, um...

11:04.214 --> 11:06.214
Listening for...

11:06.382 --> 11:08.175
Little green men.

11:15.933 --> 11:19.519
One down, a couple billion to go.

11:22.273 --> 11:23.940
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

11:36.204 --> 11:38.163
Arecibo, right?

11:39.332 --> 11:40.499
Does it show?

11:41.125 --> 11:42.375
Yeah.

11:42.543 --> 11:44.836
- Cracker Jack?
- No, thanks.

11:45.004 --> 11:46.546
- Mind if I sit down?
- Sure.

11:48.216 --> 11:52.219
I hear the locals, they call it El Radar.

11:52.386 --> 11:55.222
Convinced it has
some dark military purpose.

11:55.389 --> 11:56.807
I think we're pretty harmless.

11:58.267 --> 11:59.392
Palmer Joss.

12:00.228 --> 12:02.687
- Ellie Arroway.
- Nice to meet you, Ellie.

12:03.898 --> 12:06.858
What are you studying up there?

12:08.528 --> 12:09.903
The usual.

12:10.071 --> 12:13.114
You know. Nebulae, quasars, pulsars,
stuff like that.

12:13.282 --> 12:15.867
What are you...? What are you writing?

12:16.035 --> 12:20.413
The usual. Nouns, adverbs,
adjective here and there.

12:21.749 --> 12:23.250
I work on a project called SETI.

12:24.043 --> 12:26.086
Search for Extraterrestrial Intelligence?

12:26.754 --> 12:30.339
Wow. Man, that is out there.

12:31.132 --> 12:32.967
Wait, are you a student or something?

12:33.134 --> 12:36.428
Mm-mm. I'm a writer. I'm writing a book.

12:36.596 --> 12:41.267
Down here doing research about how
technology affects Third World cultures.

12:41.434 --> 12:44.270
I'm also looking for this guy
David Drumlin.

12:44.437 --> 12:48.899
He's the new head of the National Science
Foundation. I'm trying to get an interview.

12:49.776 --> 12:52.778
- I take it you know him?
- Mm-hm.

12:52.946 --> 12:54.905
You could say that.

12:55.740 --> 12:59.410
SETI, man. That's fringe.

12:59.578 --> 13:01.120
I've crossed paths with this guy.

13:01.288 --> 13:03.956
Something like that
must really chap his ass, huh?

13:06.918 --> 13:08.294
Compass.

13:09.963 --> 13:11.547
For you, EI.

13:16.136 --> 13:17.928
You better keep this.

13:18.805 --> 13:20.931
Might save your life someday.

13:25.103 --> 13:26.896
Will you have dinner with me tonight?

13:28.440 --> 13:29.773
I...

13:29.941 --> 13:33.569
I don't make a very good research subject.
I'm just not very quotable.

13:33.737 --> 13:37.489
No quotes. No quotes. Scout's honor.
Just a good meal, good company.

13:38.325 --> 13:40.159
I gotta go.

13:43.371 --> 13:45.497
But, uh...

13:48.793 --> 13:51.128
Drumlirs coming in this Tuesday.

13:59.511 --> 14:03.389
Now I remember why I took that desk job.

14:04.391 --> 14:06.935
- Dr. Drumlin, how are you?
- Dr. Drumlin.

14:07.895 --> 14:09.979
Glad you could make it, David.

14:10.439 --> 14:13.691
If I'd known it was gonna take
three planes, I might've reconsidered.

14:13.859 --> 14:15.234
How is that new office?

14:15.402 --> 14:19.989
I'm still settling in. They already wanna take
half my budget and give it to the Pentagon.

14:20.157 --> 14:23.034
Ellie. Still waiting for E.T. To call?

14:23.202 --> 14:27.205
- Well, I understand we're having a little...
- Good to see you too.

14:27.373 --> 14:28.373
Asshole.

14:28.540 --> 14:30.875
Uh-oh. Looks like
it's gonna be a long night.

14:31.043 --> 14:35.505
Science must first be accountable to the
people who are paying for it, the taxpayers.

14:35.673 --> 14:39.050
We need to stop wasting money
on pie-in-the-sky abstractions...

14:39.218 --> 14:42.178
...and start spending it on practical,
measurable ways...

14:42.346 --> 14:45.223
...to improve the lives of the people
who are footing the bill.

14:45.391 --> 14:48.518
Not unlike my L-band,
globular-clusters work.

14:48.686 --> 14:51.729
Wait, you're saying you wanna do away
with all pure research now?

14:51.897 --> 14:55.233
What's wrong with science being practical?
Even profitable?

14:55.442 --> 14:59.278
Nothing, as long as your motive
is the search for truth.

14:59.446 --> 15:02.573
Which is exactly what
the pursuit of science is.

15:04.118 --> 15:05.952
That's a rather interesting position...

15:06.120 --> 15:09.789
...coming from a man on a crusade
against the evils of technology...

15:09.957 --> 15:11.040
...Father Joss.

15:11.709 --> 15:14.085
PALMER:
I'm not against technology, doctor.

15:14.253 --> 15:18.505
I'm against the men who deify it
at the expense of human truth.

15:22.343 --> 15:25.554
Kent, I've been meaning to have
a word with you. Over here, please.

15:25.722 --> 15:27.597
KENT:
Yeah, I'll just...

15:31.602 --> 15:34.730
I think that hurt my chances
with that interview. What do you think?

15:35.356 --> 15:37.190
You're a priest?

15:38.693 --> 15:39.943
No, not really.

15:40.611 --> 15:43.697
I got my Masters in Divinity...

15:43.865 --> 15:47.451
...then dropped out of seminary to
do some secular humanitarian work...

15:47.618 --> 15:50.120
...coordinating efforts
for Third World churches.

15:50.705 --> 15:53.373
I couldn't live with
the whole celibacy thing.

15:55.752 --> 15:57.127
You could...

15:57.295 --> 15:59.880
You could call me a man of the cloth...

16:00.715 --> 16:02.299
...without the cloth.

16:05.636 --> 16:07.304
You wanna get out of here?

16:09.223 --> 16:12.726
All right, you see that sort of large,
W-shaped constellation right there?

16:12.894 --> 16:14.352
That's Cassiopeia.

16:14.520 --> 16:19.066
And Cassiopeia A gives off
a whole lot of radio signals.

16:19.233 --> 16:23.737
I actually listen to them a lot.
It's a remnant of a supernova.

16:24.447 --> 16:27.324
When did you know
you wanted to be an astronomer?

16:27.825 --> 16:29.284
Well, when I...

16:29.452 --> 16:33.288
When I was about 8 years old,
I was watching the sunset...

16:33.456 --> 16:36.833
...and I asked my dad,
"What's that bright star over there?"

16:37.001 --> 16:39.669
Dad, what's that star there?

16:40.253 --> 16:43.339
And he said that it wasrt
really a star at all. It was actually...

16:43.507 --> 16:45.174
That's not a star, it's a planet.

16:45.342 --> 16:46.967
- A whole planet called Venus...

16:47.135 --> 16:49.136
That's the planet Venus.

16:51.473 --> 16:55.434
- Which should be over there soon.

16:55.602 --> 16:58.312
He said,
"You know why they called it Venus?

16:58.480 --> 17:01.774
Because they thought
it was so beautiful and glowing.

17:01.942 --> 17:04.026
But what they didn't know...

17:04.194 --> 17:06.820
...is that it's filled with...

17:08.031 --> 17:11.742
...deadly gases and sulfuric acid rain."

17:12.786 --> 17:16.997
"Wow," I thought,
"This is it! I'm hooked."

17:18.541 --> 17:22.545
You know, there are four hundred billion
stars out there...

17:22.712 --> 17:24.964
...just in our galaxy alone.

17:25.298 --> 17:29.218
If only one out of a million
of those had planets...

17:29.386 --> 17:32.555
...all right, and ifjust one
out of a million of those had life...

17:32.722 --> 17:37.351
...and ifjust one out of a million
of those had intelligent life...

17:37.644 --> 17:42.648
...there would be literally millions
of civilizations out there.

17:44.067 --> 17:46.152
Well, if there wasrt...

17:46.570 --> 17:49.071
...it'd be an awful waste of space.

17:54.661 --> 17:56.412
Amen.

18:04.753 --> 18:09.757
PALMER: So I was lying there,
just looking at the sky.

18:12.678 --> 18:16.514
And then I felt something. I don't know, I...

18:17.016 --> 18:19.893
All I know is that I wasrt alone.

18:20.060 --> 18:24.981
And for the first time in my life
I wasrt scared of nothing, you know?

18:25.149 --> 18:27.108
Not even dying.

18:32.448 --> 18:34.490
It was God.

18:36.952 --> 18:39.287
And there's no chance that...

18:39.455 --> 18:43.708
...you had this experience because
some part of you needed to have it?

18:44.960 --> 18:48.463
I mean, I'm a reasonably intelligent guy,
but this...

18:51.300 --> 18:55.303
No, this... No, my intellect,
it couldn't even touch this.

18:55.471 --> 18:56.512
No.

18:58.974 --> 19:01.559
I've been to Sunday school a few times.

19:02.978 --> 19:04.729
Uh-huh. And?

19:04.897 --> 19:10.151
Well, I just kept asking all these
really annoying questions like:

19:10.319 --> 19:13.279
"All right, then where did Mrs. Cain
come from?"

19:14.573 --> 19:17.158
And pretty soon they called my dad
and they asked him...

19:17.326 --> 19:20.078
...if he wouldn't mind just
keeping me home from now on.

19:20.246 --> 19:22.288
Your dad...

19:23.249 --> 19:26.459
- Is it this guy?
- Yeah.

19:28.336 --> 19:30.796
You're close to him, aren't you?

19:31.673 --> 19:35.133
Yeah, I was.
He died when I was 9 years old.

19:37.011 --> 19:39.012
I never got to know my mother.

19:40.598 --> 19:41.932
I'm sorry.

19:46.437 --> 19:48.355
That's gotta be tough.

19:50.566 --> 19:52.234
Yeah.

19:52.860 --> 19:54.861
Being alone.

20:03.371 --> 20:04.621
What do you say...

20:04.831 --> 20:08.333
...we pack a picnic tomorrow morning
and hike up to old Mount Arecibo?

20:09.210 --> 20:12.212
I don't think I can. I gotta work.

20:14.007 --> 20:17.634
All right, how about dinner, then,
tomorrow night? I know a great dive.

20:17.802 --> 20:19.761
I don't think so.

20:24.058 --> 20:27.227
- Ellie, did I miss something?
- Huh?

20:28.354 --> 20:31.565
No. Shit, I'm late.

20:32.525 --> 20:36.111
I told Kent that I'd be there at 10:30.

20:38.072 --> 20:39.865
You know, I'm not trying to push you.

20:40.074 --> 20:42.492
No, no. I've wanted to look at
this sector for weeks.

20:42.660 --> 20:47.914
Just hang out and sleep in.
And there's a bunch of food in the fridge.

20:48.082 --> 20:49.249
Okay?

20:49.417 --> 20:51.251
How can I reach you?

20:51.918 --> 20:54.420
Just leave your number. I'll call you.

21:15.901 --> 21:16.942
YOUNG ELLIE:
Dad!

21:18.987 --> 21:21.989
Dad, it's starting, you're gonna miss it.

21:25.118 --> 21:27.411
Dad, there's another one. Hurry up.

21:27.579 --> 21:29.955
TED:
In a minute, Sparks. I'm almost done.

21:30.123 --> 21:32.958
There's another one.
Come on, hurry up, Dad!

21:35.003 --> 21:37.004
[CLATTERING]

21:38.298 --> 21:52.895
Dad?

22:03.031 --> 22:04.115
Daddy?

22:17.086 --> 22:26.511
Dad.

22:28.514 --> 22:30.432
I'll get the medicine.

23:46.007 --> 23:47.674
Ellie.

23:49.260 --> 23:51.929
I know it's hard to understand this now...

23:52.931 --> 23:57.434
...but we aren't always meant to know
why things happen the way they do.

23:57.977 --> 24:02.314
Sometimes we just have to accept it
as God's will.

24:04.275 --> 24:07.945
I should have kept some medicine
in the downstairs bathroom.

24:08.112 --> 24:10.656
Then I could've gotten to it sooner.

24:26.631 --> 24:29.091
[CHATTERING]

24:36.182 --> 24:37.849
YOUNG ELLIE:
CQ...

24:38.685 --> 24:41.979
...this is W-9 GFO. Do you copy?

24:45.149 --> 24:47.818
Dad, this is Ellie. Come back.

24:50.989 --> 24:53.031
This is Eleanor Arroway...

24:53.199 --> 24:56.785
...transmitting on 14.2 megahertz.

24:59.289 --> 25:00.872
Dad.

25:02.916 --> 25:04.417
Are you there?

25:06.545 --> 25:08.004
Come back.

25:10.924 --> 25:12.341
Dad.

25:14.720 --> 25:16.178
Are you there?

25:17.222 --> 25:18.723
Dad, this is Ellie.

25:27.733 --> 25:30.234
[BEEPING]

25:48.086 --> 25:50.046
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

25:50.213 --> 25:51.505
Ellie.

25:51.673 --> 25:55.051
Hi, Kent. What are you doing
up so early, huh?

25:55.719 --> 25:57.053
I was thinking...

25:57.763 --> 25:59.305
...we'd make a pretty good team.

25:59.473 --> 26:00.514
What?

26:00.682 --> 26:04.185
We could put together
a kick-ass ad-hoc SETI program.

26:04.394 --> 26:06.604
You know the Very Large Array
in New Mexico?

26:06.772 --> 26:09.231
It would be a dynamite place
to do serious SETI...

26:09.399 --> 26:12.068
What are you talking about, Kent?

26:13.528 --> 26:15.404
Drumlin pulled the plug.

26:16.031 --> 26:17.156
We're homeless.

26:27.750 --> 26:29.542
Hey, watch it.

26:31.295 --> 26:33.213
ELLIE:
Is it true, huh? Did you pull the plug?

26:33.381 --> 26:35.757
You can't see it now,
but I'm doing you a favor.

26:35.925 --> 26:40.095
You are far too promising a scientist
to be wasting your gifts on this nonsense.

26:40.262 --> 26:42.263
Look, I don't consider what could be...

26:42.473 --> 26:45.475
...the most important discovery
of the human race nonsense, okay?

26:45.643 --> 26:47.060
There's 400 billion stars...

26:47.228 --> 26:50.105
And two probabilities.
One, there is intelligent life...

26:50.314 --> 26:53.316
...but it's so far away you'll
never contact it in your lifetime.

26:53.484 --> 26:55.694
- And two!
- You're making a decision...

26:55.861 --> 27:00.281
There's nothing but noble gases and carbon
compounds and you're wasting your time.

27:00.449 --> 27:03.535
In the meantime, you won't be published,
won't be taken seriously.

27:03.703 --> 27:05.412
And your career will be over.

27:05.579 --> 27:08.957
So what? It's my life.

27:45.995 --> 27:48.872
Hey, Kent. You were right.

27:49.039 --> 27:52.750
Screw Drumlin. We're gonna raise
the money. We're going to New Mexico.

27:52.917 --> 27:55.461
KENT: Chicago has all the stuff,
but let me know how it goes.

27:55.628 --> 27:58.505
I've got some more corporate stops
on the East Coast for you.

27:58.673 --> 28:01.842
Hey, Fish, did that investor from Houston
ever get back to us?

28:02.010 --> 28:04.011
FISHER:
I'm gonna hit him up on my way to L.A.

28:04.220 --> 28:06.346
ELLIE: Try begging for some of that
Hollywood money.

28:06.556 --> 28:10.142
Why not? They've been making money
off of aliens for years, right?

28:10.310 --> 28:13.145
- Begging is good for the soul.
- We'll see about that.

28:13.313 --> 28:14.980
- Just do me a favor.
- Yeah.

28:15.148 --> 28:17.941
Try not to be too confrontational.

28:18.109 --> 28:20.569
Huh? Confrontational? Me?
What do you mean?

28:20.737 --> 28:22.362
I'm gonna see if I left anything.

28:55.730 --> 28:59.566
ELLIE: This is a unique time in our history,
in the history of any civilization.

28:59.734 --> 29:02.528
It's the moment
of the acquisition of technology.

29:02.737 --> 29:05.572
That's the moment
where contact becomes possible.

29:06.282 --> 29:11.119
The Very Large Array in New Mexico
is the key to our chances for success.

29:11.287 --> 29:13.538
With its 27 linked radio telescopes...

29:13.705 --> 29:17.083
...we can search more accurately
than at any other conventional facility.

29:17.251 --> 29:22.421
Now, we've gotten approval to buy
the telescope time from the government.

29:22.923 --> 29:25.091
Now all we really need is the money.

29:25.884 --> 29:27.885
A nice presentation, doctor.

29:28.595 --> 29:33.099
But while our foundation arm has a mandate
to support experimental programs...

29:33.267 --> 29:37.228
...we must confess that
your proposal seems less like science...

29:37.396 --> 29:39.105
...and more like science fiction.

29:41.608 --> 29:43.067
Science fiction.

29:46.488 --> 29:48.281
You're right.

29:48.740 --> 29:50.324
It's crazy.

29:51.118 --> 29:54.078
In fact, it's even worse than that: Nuts.

29:55.622 --> 29:57.123
You wanna hear something nutty?

29:57.291 --> 29:59.959
A couple guys wanted to build
something called an airplane.

30:00.127 --> 30:03.296
You get people to go in it and fly like birds.
Ridiculous, right?

30:03.463 --> 30:05.423
Or what about
breaking the sound barrier...

30:05.591 --> 30:09.218
...or rockets to the moon,
or atomic energy or a mission to Mars?

30:09.428 --> 30:11.262
Science fiction, right?

30:11.430 --> 30:12.555
Look.

30:12.723 --> 30:16.976
All I'm asking is for you to
just have the tiniest bit of vision.

30:17.144 --> 30:20.730
You know, to just step back for one minute
and look at the big picture.

30:20.898 --> 30:22.356
To take a chance on something...

30:22.524 --> 30:26.152
...which might end up being
the most profoundly impactful moment...

30:26.320 --> 30:30.489
...for humanity, for the history of history.

30:33.702 --> 30:35.244
I'm sorry.

30:36.371 --> 30:37.996
I just spent the last 13 months...

30:38.664 --> 30:42.000
...coming into rooms like this
and talking to people like you.

30:42.418 --> 30:45.128
The truth is, you're my last chance, so...

30:45.296 --> 30:46.755
I'm sorry I wasted your time.

30:46.923 --> 30:48.214
Doctor.

30:48.382 --> 30:58.850
Yes, sir.

31:01.938 --> 31:03.146
You have your money.

31:06.192 --> 31:10.987
Thank you.

31:39.350 --> 31:41.851
[MOTOR HUMMING]

31:57.535 --> 32:01.578
MAN:
Oh! Perfect cast. Come on, fishy.

32:01.746 --> 32:05.416
Frank, look at the size
of that son of a bitch!

32:17.846 --> 32:19.930
Welcome back, Dr. C.

32:20.098 --> 32:21.598
How'd it go?

32:22.267 --> 32:25.519
- How was the trip?
- I've had better.

32:26.021 --> 32:29.106
Drumlin. What is this?
This his personal vendetta now?

32:29.274 --> 32:33.193
It's not just Drumlin. There's been enormous
pressure from other scientists as well.

32:33.361 --> 32:36.613
It doesn't matter anyway,
Hadders funding us for another two years.

32:36.781 --> 32:39.950
Uh... These are government-owned
telescopes, they can lease to whomever.

32:40.118 --> 32:43.912
And they don't want the high priestess
of the desert using them anymore.

32:44.748 --> 32:45.789
What?

32:45.957 --> 32:49.293
Staring at static on TV for hours,
listening to washing machines.

32:49.461 --> 32:51.837
Did you really think these stories
wouldn't get out?

32:52.005 --> 32:55.758
- I was looking for patterns in the chaos.
- Doesrt matter, we're a joke to them.

32:55.925 --> 32:57.468
They want us out.

32:58.928 --> 33:02.264
We've got three months
until the paperwork goes through.

33:04.976 --> 33:08.145
Fine. I'll start looking for other funding.
I'll just start...

33:08.313 --> 33:12.816
Could you face reality, please?
Just this once, Ellie. We lost.

33:12.984 --> 33:14.651
It's over.

33:20.992 --> 33:22.659
Fine.

33:22.827 --> 33:24.827
But I'm not stopping.

33:24.995 --> 33:27.997
If I have to go it alone, I'll go it alone.
I've done it before.

34:17.755 --> 34:21.509
My guest tonight is author
and theologian Palmer Joss.

34:21.677 --> 34:26.681
He's become a spiritual counselor of sorts
and a recent fixture at the White House.

34:26.849 --> 34:29.809
"God's Diplomat,"
according to The New York Times.

34:30.018 --> 34:33.688
His latest book, Losing Faith,
is currently number one...

34:33.897 --> 34:36.232
...on that publicatiors bestseller list.

34:36.400 --> 34:37.900
Thanks for being with us, Palmer.

34:38.068 --> 34:40.862
You have had quite a ride
this last couple of years.

34:41.029 --> 34:43.489
Yeah, I sure have, Larry.

34:43.657 --> 34:46.159
You know, Fish, I was thinking.

34:46.326 --> 34:50.661
Who would make the best astronomers?
I mean, think about it.

34:50.830 --> 34:56.835
Who has the perfect synthesis
of career and lifestyle?

34:57.003 --> 34:59.921
- I give.
- Vampires!

35:00.089 --> 35:02.507
Are you anti-technology?
Are you anti-science?

35:02.675 --> 35:04.676
PALMER:
No, not at all.

35:04.844 --> 35:07.721
The question that I'm asking is this:

35:08.389 --> 35:11.099
Are we happier as a human race?

35:11.267 --> 35:16.188
Is the world fundamentally a better place
because of science and technology?

35:16.898 --> 35:19.357
We shop at home, we surf the Web...

35:19.567 --> 35:22.360
...but at the same time we feel emptier...

35:22.528 --> 35:27.365
...and more cut off from each other
than at any other time in human history.

35:27.533 --> 35:30.202
I mean, we're becoming
a synthesized society...

35:30.369 --> 35:33.705
...in a great, big hurry
to get to the next...

35:47.094 --> 35:50.597
I think it's because we're looking
for the meaning. What is the meaning?

35:50.765 --> 35:53.475
We have mindless jobs,
we take frantic vacations.

35:53.893 --> 35:56.895
Deficit finance trips to the mall
to buy more things...

35:57.104 --> 36:00.774
...that we think are gonna fill
these holes in our lives.

36:00.942 --> 36:03.485
Is it any wonder that we've lost
our sense of direction?

36:19.209 --> 36:23.963
[BUZZING AND PULSING]

36:44.359 --> 36:46.026
Holy shit.

36:59.374 --> 37:01.375
[ENGINE STARTS]

37:04.337 --> 37:10.384
Right ascension,
18 hours, 36 minutes, 56.2 seconds.

37:10.552 --> 37:15.556
Declination, plus 36 degrees,
46 minutes...

37:15.724 --> 37:18.892
...56.2 seconds!

37:20.562 --> 37:22.062
Confirm!

37:22.230 --> 37:28.152
Right ascension, 18 hours, 36 minutes,
56.2 seconds!

37:28.320 --> 37:31.155
Hey, is anybody awake in there?
I'm moving the array!

37:32.240 --> 37:35.034
- Confirm!
- Boss has a bogey!

37:35.243 --> 37:40.371
Right ascension, 18 hours,
36 minutes, 56.2 seconds.

37:40.539 --> 37:42.790
- Fish!
- We're on it.

37:42.958 --> 37:47.295
Plus 36 hours,
47 minutes and 1 second.

37:47.463 --> 37:51.215
Strong possible pulse chain
on Sub-Array 4.

37:51.425 --> 37:54.761
I'm moving the rest of them now.
I need you to confirm the coordinates.

37:54.928 --> 37:56.929
Check the status of the array.

37:57.097 --> 38:00.975
- She's doing all the dishes.
- All systems nominal.

38:05.606 --> 38:07.190
Hello.

38:07.941 --> 38:09.692
I need a full systems check.

38:09.860 --> 38:12.695
Coordinates confirmed.
Willie's checking the system now.

38:12.863 --> 38:15.865
Stay on top of the systems diagnostics.

38:16.033 --> 38:17.742
Check the reference point offsets.

38:17.951 --> 38:21.954
And I want you off-axis on 27
the second we get there.

38:22.122 --> 38:24.624
And tell Willie to break out the big boy.

38:26.210 --> 38:28.544
Copy that. Willie...

38:28.712 --> 38:29.962
Yeah. Go, Ellie.

38:30.130 --> 38:33.424
I can hear can it on the headphones.
We gotta be sure about this.

38:33.592 --> 38:36.302
Give me another array status.

38:37.721 --> 38:40.640
Her four are online,
the rest are tracking in.

38:40.808 --> 38:43.559
FISHER: Your four are online,
the rest are tracking in.

38:43.727 --> 38:46.104
But there's a bad drive on 16.

38:46.313 --> 38:48.815
Your four are online,
the rest are tracking in...

38:48.982 --> 38:51.818
...but there's a bad drive on 16.
Copy that?

38:53.070 --> 38:55.363
What do you want me to do
about the source queue?

38:55.531 --> 38:57.615
Look, forget about it and hold the queue.

38:57.783 --> 39:01.952
Go get ready to set the target frequency
to manual the second we're aligned.

39:02.161 --> 39:06.498
Do you copy? I want you to go
off-axis on 27 the second we're there.

39:06.749 --> 39:09.584
And leave the LO frequency where it is.

39:09.752 --> 39:13.046
Stay on it, Fish, don't let it get away.
If you lose it, scan the band.

39:13.214 --> 39:16.508
Run every frequency you can think of.

39:21.097 --> 39:22.806
How you doing?

39:27.019 --> 39:28.145
Talk to me, guys.

39:28.354 --> 39:32.190
Partially polarized set of moving pulses,
amplitude modulated.

39:32.358 --> 39:36.027
We're locked. Systems check out, signal
across the board. What's the frequency?

39:36.195 --> 39:39.239
4.46, 23 gigahertz.

39:40.616 --> 39:43.869
Hydrogen times pi. Told you.

39:44.036 --> 39:45.829
Strong sucker too.

39:45.997 --> 39:48.331
I got it! I got it, I got it!
I'm patched in.

39:49.041 --> 39:50.709
ELLIE:
All right, let me hear it.

39:53.838 --> 39:55.589
[PULSING]

39:55.756 --> 39:57.215
Listen to that.

39:59.469 --> 40:01.720
Make me a liar, Fish.

40:01.888 --> 40:04.556
It could be AWACS out of Kirtland
jamming us.

40:04.724 --> 40:06.099
But I'm doubting it.

40:06.267 --> 40:08.894
All right, let's see
if F.U.D.D.'s reading it too.

40:09.729 --> 40:13.064
Willie, patch it back
and give me the off-axis.

40:13.232 --> 40:14.900
- Are we recording?
- Never stopped.

40:16.986 --> 40:18.278
Thank you, Elmer.

40:18.488 --> 40:20.405
AWACS status is negative.

40:20.573 --> 40:23.407
- White Sands?
- On this frequency? No.

40:23.575 --> 40:25.075
I'm gonna punch up the darks.

40:28.246 --> 40:31.916
How's the spying tonight, guys?
Come on.

40:34.252 --> 40:36.754
FISHER: NORAD's not tracking
any snoops in this vector.

40:36.922 --> 40:38.506
Shuttle Endeavor is in sleep mode.

40:38.673 --> 40:41.175
Okay, point source confirmed.

40:41.343 --> 40:43.928
- Whatever it is, it ain't local.
- Position?

40:44.095 --> 40:46.764
WILLIE: I checked interferometry.
Somewhere in Lyra, I think.

40:46.932 --> 40:48.432
- Vega?
FISHER: Can't be.

40:48.600 --> 40:50.851
It's only 26 light years away.

40:51.019 --> 40:53.979
- What's the peak intensity?
FISHER: Coming up.

40:54.147 --> 40:55.397
ELLIE:
Vega.

40:55.565 --> 40:59.527
Vega. I scanned it a bunch of times at
Arecibo. It was negative results, always.

40:59.736 --> 41:03.113
Got it. Reading over 100 janskys.

41:03.281 --> 41:05.658
Jesus. I could pick it up on my...

41:05.825 --> 41:08.035
[PULSING STOPS]

41:08.787 --> 41:09.787
No.

41:40.318 --> 41:42.945
[PULSING]

41:43.113 --> 41:44.154
Come on.

41:46.491 --> 41:48.575
All right, it's restarting.

41:49.034 --> 41:50.785
Wait a minute. Those are numbers.

41:50.995 --> 41:54.080
That was a three,
the one before it was a two.

41:54.248 --> 41:57.667
Base-10 numbers. Just start counting now,
see how far can we get.

41:57.835 --> 41:59.460
One.

42:05.009 --> 42:06.092
WILLIE: Seven.
ELLIE: Seven.

42:08.929 --> 42:10.513
Those are primes.

42:10.681 --> 42:13.266
Two, three, five, seven,
those are all prime numbers.

42:13.434 --> 42:15.393
There's no way
that's a natural phenomenon.

42:15.561 --> 42:16.686
- Holy shit.
- Okay, okay.

42:16.854 --> 42:20.189
Let's just calm down
and pull up the star file on Vega.

42:20.733 --> 42:23.693
FISHER: It doesn't make any sense.
The system is too young...

42:23.861 --> 42:25.862
...so it can't have a planetary system...

42:26.030 --> 42:29.449
...let alone life
or a technological civilization.

42:29.617 --> 42:32.201
Maybe they didn't grow up there.
Maybe they're visiting.

42:32.369 --> 42:35.705
Spacecraft? This system is
full of debris. It would get clobbered.

42:35.873 --> 42:40.043
Well, not if they used their laser blasters
and photon torpedoes.

42:40.210 --> 42:43.630
- That's not funny.
- How else are we gonna explain it?

42:43.797 --> 42:47.008
Willie's right. If we go public with this
and we're wrong, that's it.

42:47.176 --> 42:49.677
It's over. We're cooked.

42:50.679 --> 42:53.264
God, I wish Kent was here.

42:53.432 --> 42:57.518
Whatever the signal is, we better
do something soon. Vega's gonna set.

42:58.062 --> 43:04.651
Position confirmed.
We've got 4.4623 gigahertz, confirmed.

43:04.818 --> 43:07.737
We've got 112 janskys.

43:07.905 --> 43:10.365
All right, do you have
a source location yet?

43:12.909 --> 43:15.827
We put it right smack in the middle.

43:15.995 --> 43:17.579
Vega.

43:19.415 --> 43:22.417
Okay, thanks, lan. Keep tracking
and we'll get back to you.

43:22.585 --> 43:24.252
Yeah, right-o.

43:34.430 --> 43:35.931
FISHER:
Okay, 101.

43:36.099 --> 43:40.852
The pulse sequenced through every
prime number between two and 101.

43:42.438 --> 43:44.439
Who are we gonna call now?

43:47.276 --> 43:48.360
Everybody.

43:56.119 --> 43:59.538
MAN 1 [ON TV]: The rumors are flying,
the implications extraordinary.

43:59.706 --> 44:03.333
This morning's detection of an unidentified
radio source from deep space...

44:03.501 --> 44:06.128
...can neither be confirmed nor denied.

44:06.295 --> 44:08.088
But the military presence arriving...

44:08.256 --> 44:12.134
MAN 2: Sources close to the VLA report
that the planet has been contacted...

44:12.301 --> 44:14.261
...by some form of intelligent being...

44:14.429 --> 44:17.931
...living outside of our solar system.
Again, there is no confirmation...

44:18.099 --> 44:22.018
...that the official IAU communiquÃ©
was sent from this government facility.

44:22.186 --> 44:24.896
KITZ:
I want all of these people out of here.

44:25.064 --> 44:26.857
Where's the girl?

44:31.028 --> 44:33.947
Twenty-two stations worldwide
now confirming the signal.

44:34.115 --> 44:35.906
Vega is currently below our horizon...

44:36.074 --> 44:38.534
...so what you're hearing
is the signal from-

44:38.702 --> 44:42.496
Get decryption people in here now.
Lunacharsky is visiting at Cal Tech.

44:42.664 --> 44:44.123
Explain this to me.

44:44.332 --> 44:48.210
If the source of the signal is so
sophisticated, why the remedial math?

44:48.378 --> 44:50.171
Exactly, why don't they speak English?

44:50.338 --> 44:53.549
Maybe because 70 percent of the planet
speaks other languages.

44:53.717 --> 44:56.510
Mathematics is
the only truly universal language.

44:57.220 --> 44:59.805
It's no coincidence
that they're using primes.

45:00.015 --> 45:02.224
- I don't get it.
- Prime numbers.

45:02.392 --> 45:06.187
That would be integers that are
only divisible by themselves and one.

45:09.065 --> 45:12.693
We think this may be a beacon,
some kind of an announcement...

45:12.861 --> 45:13.986
...to get our attention.

45:14.196 --> 45:17.865
If it's attention you want, you got that.
One thing: Vega.

45:18.074 --> 45:21.577
People have been looking at Vega for years
with no results.

45:21.745 --> 45:24.580
And now yesterday they start
broadcasting primes. Why?

45:24.748 --> 45:28.626
Well, it's hardly yesterday, because the
signal has been transmitting for 26 years.

45:28.794 --> 45:30.252
Dr. Arroway.

45:30.420 --> 45:34.632
- Excuse me, who are you?
- Michael Kitz, National Security Advisor.

45:34.800 --> 45:36.091
Let me first say that your...

45:36.259 --> 45:40.221
Actually, first, could you ask the gentlemen
with the firearms to wait outside?

45:40.388 --> 45:42.389
This is supposed to be a civilian facility.

45:48.855 --> 45:51.482
- Doctor, with all due respect to your...
- Excuse me.

45:51.858 --> 45:55.194
Hey, hey, hey.
Hi, I'm so glad you're back.

45:55.779 --> 45:58.988
Come on, I got something for you to hear.
Is this great?

45:59.156 --> 46:01.574
- Who are all these people?
- I have no idea.

46:01.784 --> 46:04.744
Sit down. And we could use some help
with the spectrum analysis.

46:04.912 --> 46:06.871
- Listen to that. I'll get on it.
- Headsets.

46:07.039 --> 46:09.123
So I'll just come right to the point,
shall I?

46:09.416 --> 46:13.419
Your having sent this all over the world may
constitute a breach of national security.

46:13.587 --> 46:15.255
This isn't a person-to-person call.

46:15.464 --> 46:19.968
You can't think that a civilization sending
this would intend it just for Americans.

46:20.135 --> 46:21.970
I'm saying you might have consulted us.

46:22.137 --> 46:25.932
- The contents could be extremely sensitive.
- You want to classify prime numbers?

46:26.100 --> 46:29.853
Mike, please. We're only in line
with Vega so many hours a day.

46:30.020 --> 46:34.482
The only way to monitor the signal
is to get the cooperation of other stations.

46:34.650 --> 46:39.028
If Dr. Arroway hadrt acted quickly,
we could have lost key elements.

46:39.196 --> 46:40.822
Okay, fine, they've got the primes.

46:40.990 --> 46:44.117
If you're right about there being a more
significant transmission...

46:44.285 --> 46:45.952
Which will need help
to receive and decode.

46:46.120 --> 46:47.954
Doctor, do you understand that my job
is to protect...?

46:48.122 --> 46:49.914
KENT: Shh!
- What?

46:50.082 --> 46:52.166
- Listen.
- I hear it.

46:52.334 --> 46:54.085
- Hear what?
- Harmonic.

46:54.253 --> 46:58.506
Bingo. I had Willie ask Rattan
to retune to 8.9247 gigahertz.

46:58.674 --> 47:00.174
There's a lot more here, folks.

47:00.342 --> 47:03.303
- Fish, let's get on the negative sideband.
FISHER: I'm already on it.

47:03.470 --> 47:05.054
KITZ: What is going on?
DRUMLIN: Another signal.

47:05.222 --> 47:06.556
Another signal, look at that.

47:06.724 --> 47:09.851
A second signal at double the frequency.
It looks like a...

47:10.019 --> 47:11.394
Somebody get a TV monitor.

47:11.937 --> 47:14.022
Patch the recording
into the image processor.

47:14.189 --> 47:17.483
- You want the new data?
- Yeah, the new frequency we just recorded.

47:17.693 --> 47:19.611
David, explain this to me, please.

47:19.778 --> 47:22.905
With the prime there's another signal.
Looks like a TV transmission.

47:23.072 --> 47:24.239
WILLIE:
We're hot.

47:24.407 --> 47:27.492
Do me a favor, go get the blinds.
There is a lot of glare.

47:27.660 --> 47:29.161
You're patched in.

47:29.329 --> 47:33.498
All right, it's definitely an image.
Let's try and stabilize it.

47:37.545 --> 47:39.046
What do you make of that, Fish?

47:39.213 --> 47:42.633
It's two different interlaced frames.
I'm framing one.

47:46.012 --> 47:48.764
ELLIE: It's just noise.
FISHER: Trying frame two.

47:49.515 --> 47:53.268
I've got an offset carrier here.
I think it's audio.

47:53.436 --> 47:54.686
Plug it in, plug it in.

47:59.025 --> 48:00.317
Center that segment.

48:00.485 --> 48:02.027
FISHER:
Centering.

48:05.907 --> 48:08.867
- Can you clean it up any more than that?
FISHER: I'm working on it.

48:21.881 --> 48:23.215
What the hell...?

48:24.050 --> 48:25.217
Try zooming out.

48:29.097 --> 48:30.222
All right, freeze.

48:30.390 --> 48:31.723
Reverse values.

48:33.393 --> 48:35.519
Try zooming out again.

48:39.107 --> 48:41.233
Rotate 90 degrees counterclock...

48:42.735 --> 48:44.695
DRUMLIN:
My God.

48:45.988 --> 48:49.073
[HITLER SPEAKING IN GERMAN
ON RADIO]

48:49.741 --> 48:52.702
- Okay.
KENT: What's going on?

48:52.869 --> 48:55.538
You're not gonna believe this.

49:08.969 --> 49:10.720
Does anybody speak German?

49:12.139 --> 49:14.557
"I declare the Games in Berlin...

49:15.642 --> 49:17.393
...at the celebration...

49:17.602 --> 49:21.981
...of the first Olympics of the new era
has opened."

49:32.784 --> 49:34.201
Get me the White House.

49:34.828 --> 49:37.538
Twenty million people died
defeating that son of a bitch...

49:37.706 --> 49:39.915
...and he's our first ambassador
to outer space?

49:40.083 --> 49:42.418
- Actually...
- The broadcast from the '36 Olympics...

49:42.586 --> 49:45.588
...was the first television transmission
that went into space.

49:45.756 --> 49:49.133
That they recorded it and sent it back
is saying, "Hello, we heard you."

49:49.301 --> 49:51.761
Or, "Sjeg Heil, you're our kind of people."

49:51.970 --> 49:54.638
Wait. Hitler and his politics
have nothing to do with this.

49:54.806 --> 49:58.309
It's highly unlikely they would understand,
and people need to understand...

49:58.477 --> 50:00.644
The people are in very good hands,
Dr. Arroway.

50:00.812 --> 50:01.812
We'll take it from here.

50:01.980 --> 50:04.065
WOMAN [ON TV]:
The White House has just released...

50:04.232 --> 50:05.316
Smile, folks. We're on.

50:05.484 --> 50:08.402
- A statement confirming a message
from deep space...

50:08.570 --> 50:12.655
...has been received by American scientists.
Claire Shipman is at the White House.

50:12.823 --> 50:15.992
Donna, we've been told the president
will have only a few remarks...

50:16.202 --> 50:17.660
...about today's announcement...

50:17.828 --> 50:21.247
...and that he won't be taking
any questions from the press.

50:26.212 --> 50:27.545
Good afternoon.

50:30.424 --> 50:34.636
I'm glad to be joined by my
science and technology advisor.

50:36.472 --> 50:39.307
This is the product
of years of exploration...

50:39.517 --> 50:42.727
...by some of the world's
most distinguished scientists.

50:42.937 --> 50:47.148
Like all discoveries, this one
will and should continue to be reviewed...

50:47.358 --> 50:50.110
...examined and scrutinized.

50:50.319 --> 50:53.404
It must be confirmed by other scientists.

50:53.572 --> 50:59.369
The fact that something of this magnitude
is being explored is another...

50:59.537 --> 51:03.414
Fish, what is the story over here?
I thought Ellie was supposed to be on.

51:03.624 --> 51:05.125
I don't know.

51:05.751 --> 51:08.711
Guys? Guys? Um...

51:09.505 --> 51:12.340
You know those interlaced frames
that we thought were noise?

51:13.175 --> 51:15.844
This has structure. I'm hearing structure.

51:17.221 --> 51:19.472
If this discovery is confirmed...

51:19.682 --> 51:23.309
...it will be one of the most stunning
insights into our universe...

51:23.519 --> 51:25.562
...that science has ever uncovered.

51:26.063 --> 51:31.234
Its implications are as far-reaching
and awe-inspiring as can be imagined.

51:31.443 --> 51:34.903
Even as it promises answers
to some of our oldest questions...

51:35.113 --> 51:38.532
...it poses still others,
even more fundamental.

51:38.741 --> 51:42.369
We will continue to listen closely
to what it has to say...

51:42.579 --> 51:46.123
...as we continue the search for answers
and for knowledge...

51:46.332 --> 51:52.004
...that is as old as humanity itself
but essential to our people's future.

51:52.338 --> 51:53.797
- Thank you.
MAN: Sir...

51:53.965 --> 51:56.091
Is there a considerable
global security threat?

51:56.259 --> 51:59.386
I'll answer your questions at the end,
but first a few corrections.

51:59.554 --> 52:03.557
The message was received Friday morning,
6:31 a.m. Mountain Standard Time.

52:03.766 --> 52:08.353
It was largely mathematical, and in spite of
reports you may have seen to the contrary...

52:08.521 --> 52:11.064
...appears to be completely benign
in nature.

52:11.274 --> 52:15.027
Let me say that again.
The message is completely benign.

52:15.195 --> 52:18.697
The president has been in touch
with heads of state from around the world...

52:18.865 --> 52:21.617
...and every possible security measure
is being taken.

52:21.784 --> 52:24.828
To better explain to you
the events of the last 48 hours...

52:25.038 --> 52:29.458
...l'm turning you over to the leader of the
team that made this remarkable discovery...

52:29.626 --> 52:33.795
...Dr. David Drumlin,
special science advisor to the president.

52:41.721 --> 52:44.556
Thank you, Rachel. Hello.

52:46.476 --> 52:48.936
In 1936
a very faint television signal...

52:49.145 --> 52:52.231
...transmitted the opening ceremonies
of the Olympic Games...

52:52.398 --> 52:56.068
...as a show
of German superior technology.

52:57.152 --> 52:59.237
That signal left Earth
at the speed of light...

52:59.404 --> 53:01.405
[PHONE RINGING]

53:01.573 --> 53:05.409
...and 26 years later arrived in the vicinity
of the star we call Vega.

53:06.328 --> 53:10.164
That signal has been sent back to us
hugely amplified...

53:10.332 --> 53:13.000
...an unmistakable sign of intelligence.

53:13.168 --> 53:14.669
ELLIE:
You're online, Kent, go ahead.

53:14.836 --> 53:19.048
KENT: The Adolf transmission used 25 frames
per second but we're receiving 50.

53:19.216 --> 53:23.177
So we canned the other 25
through a series of search algorithms.

53:23.345 --> 53:25.888
We found a series of markers
on the top of each frame.

53:26.056 --> 53:27.765
- Are you ready?
- Yeah, go ahead.

53:27.933 --> 53:31.185
- Send it, Willie.
WILLIE: Okay, here it comes.

53:34.439 --> 53:35.773
KENT:
It's digital...

53:35.941 --> 53:40.194
...massive amounts of data which
extend right to the higher harmonics.

53:40.862 --> 53:42.613
Jackpot.

53:43.532 --> 53:45.449
ELLIE:
All right, as you'll see...

53:45.617 --> 53:48.911
...interlaced with the frames
of the original Hitler image...

53:49.079 --> 53:52.039
...we found these sections.

53:52.207 --> 53:55.710
Now, we thought they were just noise,
but they're actually data...

53:55.877 --> 53:57.169
...huge amounts of it.

53:57.337 --> 54:01.882
When we combine this with the data from
the amplification of the original signal...

54:02.050 --> 54:05.344
...we get these encrypted pages of text.

54:05.554 --> 54:09.724
Now, no two are alike and
we've uncovered over 10,000 already.

54:09.891 --> 54:12.310
What does it mean, doctor?

54:12.477 --> 54:14.812
Well, we have no idea.
It could be anything.

54:14.980 --> 54:17.690
It could be the first volume
of an Encyclopedia Galactica.

54:17.858 --> 54:20.775
Instructions to acquaint us
with their colonization procedures.

54:20.943 --> 54:22.902
Moses with a few billion
new commandments.

54:23.070 --> 54:25.363
How long will it take to decode it?

54:25.573 --> 54:28.908
It could take forever.
We really need a primer...

54:29.076 --> 54:32.162
We need to get the best
decryption people we have.

54:32.663 --> 54:36.916
I intend to use the VLA
as my command post.

54:37.084 --> 54:40.503
In the meantime, my office
has made out a preliminary budget.

54:40.671 --> 54:44.632
Wait a minute.
This is a privately-funded operation.

54:44.842 --> 54:47.135
We're only leasing dish time
from the government...

54:47.345 --> 54:50.430
If there's a more clear case
of eminent domain, I've never seen it.

54:50.598 --> 54:53.183
I'm going to recommend
we militarize this project.

54:53.351 --> 54:55.727
What? This is my project.

54:55.895 --> 54:59.272
Nobody knows more about these scenarios
than I do. David, tell them...

54:59.440 --> 55:02.817
Excuse me, could we calm down here?

55:03.027 --> 55:07.697
Now, I'm going to recommend that
Dr. Drumlin coordinate the decryption effort.

55:07.865 --> 55:11.242
However, in light of Dr. Arroway's
long experience in these matters...

55:11.410 --> 55:15.622
...for the time being, she will continue
to direct operations at the VLA...

55:15.790 --> 55:20.460
...understanding that future discoveries
will be kept in strictest confidence...

55:20.628 --> 55:22.545
...until such time as the president...

55:22.713 --> 55:26.716
...can decide the most suitable
course of action. Understood?

55:26.884 --> 55:28.093
Yes.

55:28.386 --> 55:31.012
MAN:
This is CNN Breaking News.

55:31.180 --> 55:34.140
The president made a statement,
calling the message from Vega...

55:34.350 --> 55:36.476
...one of the most stunning insights
into our...

55:36.685 --> 55:41.689
Attendance at religious services has
risen a dramatic 39 percent in recent days.

55:41.857 --> 55:45.692
...as police in three German divisions
clashed with neo-Nazi protesters.

55:45.860 --> 55:47.986
So it turns out
there's life on other planets.

55:48.196 --> 55:51.824
Boy, this is really gonna change
the Miss Universe contest.

55:52.492 --> 55:56.829
Health officials from around the world are
concerned that the message from Vega...

55:56.996 --> 55:59.623
...might trigger a rash of mass suicides...

55:59.833 --> 56:02.459
...not unlike the recent cult deaths
near San Diego...

56:02.669 --> 56:04.628
Even a scientist has to admit...

56:04.838 --> 56:09.341
...that there are some pretty serious
religious overtones to all this.

56:09.509 --> 56:11.677
Let's hear from someone
whose organization...

56:11.886 --> 56:14.430
...has been accused of conducting
its own inquisition:

56:14.597 --> 56:17.224
Richard Rank,
head of the Conservative coalition.

56:17.392 --> 56:18.475
Thank you.

56:18.643 --> 56:23.021
This is yet another example of science
intruding into matters of faith.

56:24.065 --> 56:27.359
This means they
have been reacting to TV signals...

56:27.569 --> 56:30.487
...they got from the 1930s.
They're just getting them.

56:30.697 --> 56:34.366
Imagine how disappointed
they're gonna be if they're Cubs fans.

56:34.534 --> 56:37.703
We now take you to Jeremy Roth,
who is reporting on events...

56:37.912 --> 56:41.373
...at the Very Large Array
near Socorro, New Mexico.

56:41.583 --> 56:43.417
Like a bolt from the blue it came.

56:43.585 --> 56:47.754
The message from Vega has caused
thousands of believers and non-believers...

56:47.922 --> 56:51.842
...to descend upon the VLA facility
here in the desert of New Mexico.

56:52.051 --> 56:54.553
Many have come to protest,
many to pray...

56:54.721 --> 56:59.558
...but most have come to participate
in what has become the best show in town.

57:06.191 --> 57:09.317
[CHATTERING]

57:26.418 --> 57:28.336
[CHANTING]

57:59.576 --> 58:05.456
That's right. I'll be there in Vega,
thank you very much.

58:08.460 --> 58:11.379
CHORUS [SINGING]: Hajl to Vega
Hail to Vega, Hail to Vega

58:11.547 --> 58:14.799
Hail to Vega

58:16.134 --> 58:17.802
But they have failed!

58:18.387 --> 58:20.930
It's the same people who,
again and again...

58:21.098 --> 58:23.516
...have brought us
to the brink of destruction.

58:23.725 --> 58:27.770
Who've polluted our air,
who've poisoned our water.

58:28.981 --> 58:30.982
Now these scientists...

58:31.983 --> 58:33.817
...have had their chance.

58:33.985 --> 58:37.404
Are these the kind of people...

58:37.572 --> 58:40.699
...that you want
talking to your God for you?

58:40.866 --> 58:42.826
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

58:45.162 --> 58:47.247
MAN [ON TV]:
Efforts continue around the clock.

58:47.582 --> 58:51.167
But for now, almost 2 full weeks
after the message's arrival...

58:51.335 --> 58:54.504
...scientists here at the VLA
still have no answers...

58:54.672 --> 58:56.423
...only more questions.

58:56.591 --> 59:00.302
Jeremy Roth, CNN,
Soccorro, New Mexico.

59:00.469 --> 59:03.805
More on the quest
for the message's meaning, after this.

59:06.642 --> 59:08.393
They gotta line up somehow.

59:08.561 --> 59:10.520
Yeah, well, this one doesn't fit, either.

59:10.688 --> 59:13.356
We've tried over a million permutations.

59:13.524 --> 59:17.027
Always, I can only get
three corners to fit.

59:18.029 --> 59:20.155
I don't understand their significance.

01:00:02.030 --> 01:00:04.740
What...? Somebody broke in...

01:00:06.743 --> 01:00:08.786
[PHONE RINGS]

01:00:11.081 --> 01:00:12.247
Hello?

01:00:13.166 --> 01:00:16.585
Hey, listen, I don't know who you are,
but you broke into the database...

01:00:19.422 --> 01:00:21.131
What? Now?

01:00:23.593 --> 01:00:24.760
Where?

01:00:24.928 --> 01:00:26.845
[FAX MACHINE HUMMING]

01:00:37.774 --> 01:00:39.191
I'll be there.

01:01:06.803 --> 01:01:08.137
MAN 1:
You should feel fortunate.

01:01:08.888 --> 01:01:10.389
He hardly lands for anyone.

01:01:41.962 --> 01:01:43.921
MAN 2:
Dr. Arroway...

01:01:47.843 --> 01:01:49.177
...I presume?

01:01:50.471 --> 01:01:51.596
Mr. Hadden.

01:01:52.890 --> 01:01:56.142
I've had my eye on you
a long time, doctor.

01:01:56.935 --> 01:02:00.438
I consider you one of my
most valuable long-term investments.

01:02:02.316 --> 01:02:04.692
And when it comes to my investments...

01:02:06.487 --> 01:02:09.155
...I always do my homework.

01:02:13.869 --> 01:02:15.620
Eleanor Ann Arroway...

01:02:15.829 --> 01:02:18.331
...born 25th August, 1964...

01:02:18.540 --> 01:02:20.124
...De Pere, Wisconsin.

01:02:20.334 --> 01:02:24.545
Mother, Joanna, died
from complications during childbirth.

01:02:25.255 --> 01:02:27.965
Early testing indicated
high predisposition...

01:02:28.133 --> 01:02:31.219
...towards science and mathematics.

01:02:31.887 --> 01:02:33.054
Father, Theodore...

01:02:33.222 --> 01:02:36.766
...advised to provide
enrichment activities along these lines...

01:02:36.975 --> 01:02:39.727
...did so conscientiously
until his death...

01:02:39.895 --> 01:02:44.564
...from myocardial infarction,
November 10, 1974.

01:02:45.149 --> 01:02:48.401
You graduated from
high school in 1979...

01:02:48.569 --> 01:02:50.695
...almost two full years early.

01:02:52.114 --> 01:02:56.493
Awarded full scholarship, M.I. T,
graduated magna cum laude.

01:02:57.453 --> 01:02:59.162
Doctoral work, Cal Tech...

01:02:59.372 --> 01:03:02.707
...where you did breakthrough work
on the lanthanide-doped ruby maser...

01:03:02.875 --> 01:03:07.003
...dramatically increasing
the sensitivity of radio telescopes.

01:03:07.338 --> 01:03:11.049
Subsequently offered a teaching position
at Harvard University...

01:03:11.259 --> 01:03:14.344
...which you turned down
to pursue SETI work...

01:03:14.554 --> 01:03:17.973
...at the Arecibo Observatory
in Puerto Rico.

01:03:20.393 --> 01:03:26.648
Changes in NSF policy
gave rise to certain funding problems...

01:03:27.733 --> 01:03:31.736
...at which point
you came to my attention.

01:03:33.072 --> 01:03:35.282
You compromised our security codes.

01:03:37.743 --> 01:03:39.578
Once upon a time...

01:03:41.581 --> 01:03:43.832
...I was a hell of an engineer.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:46.418
Please, sit, doctor.

01:03:46.586 --> 01:03:51.715
I have guests so rarely, it's important to me
that they feel welcome in my home.

01:03:52.300 --> 01:03:54.050
You live here?

01:03:55.261 --> 01:03:58.597
I find it convenient
to keep my interests...

01:03:59.765 --> 01:04:00.891
...mobile.

01:04:03.477 --> 01:04:08.397
Anyway, I've had my fill
of life on the ground.

01:04:08.899 --> 01:04:11.025
Well, I... I guess I should...

01:04:11.484 --> 01:04:15.279
Well, I guess I should thank you
for having bailed me out all that time.

01:04:20.619 --> 01:04:22.745
I know a good bet when I see one.

01:04:25.123 --> 01:04:28.334
Earl Grey. No sugar, no milk, I believe.

01:04:31.296 --> 01:04:33.130
What am I doing here?

01:04:34.132 --> 01:04:36.508
[CHUCKLES]

01:04:43.475 --> 01:04:46.602
The powers that be
have been very busy lately...

01:04:47.437 --> 01:04:52.775
...falling over each other to position
themselves for the game of the millennium.

01:04:59.032 --> 01:05:01.825
Maybe I can help deal you back in.

01:05:03.078 --> 01:05:05.496
I didn't realize that I was out.

01:05:05.997 --> 01:05:08.290
No, maybe not out...

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:11.293
...but certainly being handed your hat.

01:05:16.716 --> 01:05:20.386
I've had a long time
to make enemies, doctor.

01:05:23.974 --> 01:05:27.810
And there are many governments,
business interests...

01:05:27.978 --> 01:05:31.980
...even religious leaders that
would like to see me depart this earth.

01:05:33.440 --> 01:05:35.984
And I'll grant them their wish
soon enough.

01:05:36.527 --> 01:05:40.071
But before I do,
I wish to make a small contribution.

01:05:40.823 --> 01:05:45.410
A final gesture of goodwill to the
people of this little planet that have given...

01:05:48.205 --> 01:05:50.999
From whom I have taken so much.

01:05:54.461 --> 01:05:55.920
You found the primer.

01:05:58.340 --> 01:06:00.216
Clever girl.

01:06:00.384 --> 01:06:01.426
Lights.

01:06:10.019 --> 01:06:13.187
Pages and pages of data.

01:06:13.355 --> 01:06:16.482
Over 63,000 in all.

01:06:16.650 --> 01:06:18.735
And on the perimeter of each...

01:06:18.902 --> 01:06:22.530
Alignment symbols, a registration mark,
but they don't line up.

01:06:23.115 --> 01:06:26.284
They do, if you think like a Vegan.

01:06:27.202 --> 01:06:30.204
An alien intelligence
has got be more advanced...

01:06:30.372 --> 01:06:34.459
...and that means efficiency
functioning on multiple levels...

01:06:34.626 --> 01:06:38.463
...and in multiple dimensions.

01:06:42.426 --> 01:06:44.844
Yes, of course!

01:06:45.012 --> 01:06:46.054
Where's the primer?

01:06:46.555 --> 01:06:47.972
You'll see.

01:06:48.474 --> 01:06:52.935
Every three-dimensional page
contains a piece of the primer.

01:06:55.104 --> 01:06:58.607
There it was all the time,
staring you in the face.

01:06:59.692 --> 01:07:03.612
Buried within the message itself
is the key to decoding it.

01:07:03.780 --> 01:07:07.032
Within the layering of the matrix,
we have these basic equations:

01:07:08.993 --> 01:07:13.038
So with this very elementary foundation,
they have given us a kind of...

01:07:13.206 --> 01:07:15.791
...general scientific vocabulary.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:18.293
We now have the symbols
for true and false...

01:07:18.503 --> 01:07:19.795
This was the key...

01:07:19.962 --> 01:07:22.464
...that allowed us
to decipher their language...

01:07:22.673 --> 01:07:26.343
...for physics, geometry, chemistry.
Next frame, Ellie.

01:07:27.553 --> 01:07:31.515
Yes, and when we apply this
to the rest of the message...

01:07:32.266 --> 01:07:33.350
...we find this.

01:07:37.939 --> 01:07:40.857
Those look like engineering schematics,
almost like blueprints.

01:07:41.025 --> 01:07:42.651
Yeah.

01:07:42.819 --> 01:07:43.902
Yes.

01:07:44.070 --> 01:07:47.364
It is our belief that
the message contains instructions...

01:07:47.573 --> 01:07:51.034
...for building something,
some kind of machine.

01:07:51.202 --> 01:07:54.329
A machine? That does what, doctor?

01:07:54.497 --> 01:07:56.706
We don't know.
It might be some type...

01:07:57.667 --> 01:08:03.213
...of advanced communication device,
or a teaching machine of some kind.

01:08:03.714 --> 01:08:07.008
Or it might turn out to be
some kind of a transport.

01:08:07.426 --> 01:08:09.886
- Transport?
- There's no proof of that.

01:08:10.054 --> 01:08:13.890
The fact is, you don't know what it does.
It could be anything.

01:08:14.058 --> 01:08:17.393
Could be a Trojan horse. We build it
and out pours the entire Vegan army.

01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:20.229
Why bother risking the personnel?
It could be a weapon.

01:08:20.438 --> 01:08:22.731
Right. Some kind of
a doomsday machine.

01:08:22.899 --> 01:08:25.401
Exactly. Every time they detect
a new civilization...

01:08:25.569 --> 01:08:28.028
...they fax these construction documents
from space.

01:08:28.196 --> 01:08:31.823
We poor saps build whatever this is
and blow ourselves to kingdom come.

01:08:31.992 --> 01:08:34.910
There's no reason to believe
that their intentions are hostile.

01:08:35.078 --> 01:08:39.415
Why is the default position of the egghead
set that aliens would always be benign?

01:08:39.582 --> 01:08:42.042
- Why is that, doctor?
- We pose no threat to them.

01:08:42.210 --> 01:08:46.630
It would be like us going out of our way
to destroy microbes on an anthill in Africa

01:08:46.798 --> 01:08:48.381
DRUMLIN:
That's an interesting analogy.

01:08:48.800 --> 01:08:52.970
And how guilty would we feel if we
destroyed a few microbes on an anthill?

01:08:53.138 --> 01:08:55.514
I hope you're right, doctor. I really do.

01:08:55.682 --> 01:08:59.143
But right now my job is to protect
American lives from any threat.

01:08:59.310 --> 01:09:01.645
In that regard, I am obligated
to assume the worst.

01:09:01.897 --> 01:09:03.981
Well, yes, and I am forced
to agree with you.

01:09:04.149 --> 01:09:05.566
My problem is this:

01:09:06.193 --> 01:09:09.403
The content of that message
is morally ambiguous at best.

01:09:10.071 --> 01:09:13.616
Now, our internal numbers show
support for this is incredibly soft.

01:09:13.783 --> 01:09:16.452
If the president wishes
to stay this course...

01:09:16.620 --> 01:09:19.287
...you're gonna find his numbers
going south like a duck.

01:09:19.456 --> 01:09:21.874
- This is nuts.
RANK: Excuse me...

01:09:22.042 --> 01:09:23.459
...miss.

01:09:23.627 --> 01:09:26.002
We know nothing
of these creatures' values.

01:09:26.171 --> 01:09:28.964
The fact is, we don't even know
whether they believe in God.

01:09:29.131 --> 01:09:32.885
- This doesn't make any sense. If you...
CONSTANTINE: Excuse me, Dr. Arroway.

01:09:33.094 --> 01:09:35.554
We won't be suppressing
any opinions here today.

01:09:36.430 --> 01:09:39.140
No, of course not. I understand.

01:09:39.559 --> 01:09:41.475
What I meant to say...

01:09:41.644 --> 01:09:45.104
...is the message was written
in the language of science.

01:09:45.272 --> 01:09:48.649
Now, if it had been religious in nature,
it should have taken the form...

01:09:48.817 --> 01:09:51.444
...of a burning bush
or a booming voice from the sky.

01:09:51.654 --> 01:09:53.738
But a voice from the sky...

01:09:54.823 --> 01:09:57.659
...is exactly what you found,
Doctor Arroway.

01:10:01.038 --> 01:10:02.997
I'm sorry I'm late, ma'am.

01:10:03.165 --> 01:10:08.378
Now, I agree with Mr. Rank
that there are unavoidable...

01:10:08.587 --> 01:10:10.755
...religious implications at stake here.

01:10:10.923 --> 01:10:13.341
But that doesn't justify
taking an alarmist position.

01:10:15.386 --> 01:10:18.137
My hope here is that we can find
a common ground...

01:10:18.305 --> 01:10:21.015
...break through any obstacles
that may have kept us apart.

01:10:21.183 --> 01:10:24.602
KITZ: Well, perhaps...
- Listen, I need to make one thing very clear.

01:10:24.812 --> 01:10:29.440
Our organization will not be placated
with flowery New Age rhetoric...

01:10:30.442 --> 01:10:31.943
Mr. President.

01:10:33.404 --> 01:10:35.697
The President met
with his top advisors today...

01:10:35.864 --> 01:10:39.284
...regarding the latest efforts
to decode the message.

01:10:39.451 --> 01:10:44.122
While there has been some progress,
the official line remains a cautious one.

01:10:44.290 --> 01:10:48.918
If you're asking when we'll find out
what the purpose of that machine is...

01:10:49.920 --> 01:10:52.630
...maybe tomorrow,
maybe next year, maybe never.

01:10:57.052 --> 01:11:01.639
There he is. The man with his finger
on the spiritual pulse of the nation.

01:11:03.017 --> 01:11:06.435
- It's so good to see you, Ellie.
- You too.

01:11:07.687 --> 01:11:11.648
Your discovery, all of this.
It must be a real vindication.

01:11:12.317 --> 01:11:13.984
I'm really happy for you.

01:11:14.610 --> 01:11:18.572
- Are you?
- Mr. Joss, the president is waiting.

01:11:19.949 --> 01:11:23.076
- Okay. Yeah.
- The president is waiting.

01:11:26.998 --> 01:11:30.876
- Ellie, see you at the reception tonight?
- Yeah, I wouldn't miss it.

01:11:31.044 --> 01:11:32.919
All right, great.

01:11:42.930 --> 01:11:45.265
Excuse me, Miss Constantine,
may I speak to you?

01:11:45.433 --> 01:11:46.850
Certainly.

01:11:48.603 --> 01:11:50.812
- I have a big problem.
- Yes?

01:11:50.980 --> 01:11:52.481
Um...

01:11:52.648 --> 01:11:55.442
Do you know where I can find,
like, a really great dress?

01:12:02.450 --> 01:12:04.951
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

01:12:12.126 --> 01:12:18.965
God created man in the form of himself,
not in the form of monkeys!

01:12:20.301 --> 01:12:22.469
MAN 1: The Lord is God!
MAN 2: Praise God.

01:12:22.637 --> 01:12:26.848
MAN 3: Praise the Lord!
MAN 4: You're wasting my tax dollars!

01:12:27.642 --> 01:12:31.268
Get a job.
Don't waste my tax dollars.

01:12:31.436 --> 01:12:33.187
You hear me?

01:12:52.165 --> 01:12:53.958
Wow.

01:12:56.503 --> 01:12:58.170
You look beautiful, Ellie.

01:12:59.840 --> 01:13:02.174
- So do you.
- You really do.

01:13:05.846 --> 01:13:07.304
I read your book.

01:13:08.265 --> 01:13:09.765
Here we go.

01:13:09.933 --> 01:13:12.017
Would you like me to quote you?

01:13:12.185 --> 01:13:17.189
"Ironically, the thing that people
are most hungry for, meaning...

01:13:17.357 --> 01:13:20.693
...is the one thing that science
hasn't been able to give them."

01:13:20.861 --> 01:13:23.737
Yeah. Yeah.

01:13:24.364 --> 01:13:29.160
Come on. It's like you're saying
that science killed God.

01:13:29.327 --> 01:13:32.538
What if science simply revealed...

01:13:32.706 --> 01:13:35.207
...that he never existed
in the first place?

01:13:38.545 --> 01:13:41.714
- I think we're gonna need to get some air.
- What?

01:13:41.882 --> 01:13:43.716
And a few more of these.

01:13:45.135 --> 01:13:47.386
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:13:48.388 --> 01:13:51.557
- A little chilly out here.
- Yeah, this is nice.

01:13:51.725 --> 01:13:53.099
- I got one for you.
- What?

01:13:53.267 --> 01:13:55.018
Occam's razor. Ever heard of it?

01:13:55.227 --> 01:13:57.896
Hoccam's razor.
Sounds like some slasher movie.

01:13:58.063 --> 01:14:01.649
No, Occam's Razor.
It's a basic scientific principle. It says...

01:14:01.817 --> 01:14:05.403
...all things being equal, the simplest
explanation tends to be the right one.

01:14:05.571 --> 01:14:07.197
- Makes sense to me.
- All right.

01:14:07.364 --> 01:14:10.158
- So, what's more likely? Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:14:10.326 --> 01:14:12.952
An all-powerful, mysterious God
created the universe...

01:14:13.162 --> 01:14:15.997
...and then decided not to give
any proof of his existence?

01:14:16.165 --> 01:14:21.002
Or that he simply doesn't exist at all
and that we created him...

01:14:21.170 --> 01:14:23.671
...so we wouldn't have to feel
so small and alone.

01:14:24.590 --> 01:14:25.840
I don't know.

01:14:26.008 --> 01:14:30.011
I couldn't imagine living in a world
where God didn't exist.

01:14:30.679 --> 01:14:32.347
I wouldn't want to.

01:14:33.015 --> 01:14:35.433
How do you know that
you're not deluding yourself?

01:14:36.101 --> 01:14:39.354
I mean, for me, I'd need proof.

01:14:40.189 --> 01:14:41.689
Proof?

01:14:44.568 --> 01:14:47.070
- Did you love your father?
- What?

01:14:47.238 --> 01:14:49.030
Your dad, did you love him?

01:14:50.032 --> 01:14:52.867
Yes. Very much.

01:14:55.704 --> 01:14:57.247
Prove it.

01:15:00.042 --> 01:15:01.960
[PHONE RINGS]

01:15:03.754 --> 01:15:04.796
Kent.

01:15:04.964 --> 01:15:05.964
[PAGER BEEPING]

01:15:06.131 --> 01:15:09.133
- The White House.
- Mr. Joss.

01:15:10.302 --> 01:15:13.263
DRUMLIN: I don't want excuses.
Whoever is responsible, I want their head.

01:15:13.430 --> 01:15:16.390
- Ellie?
- What happened?

01:15:16.558 --> 01:15:17.975
You were right all along.

01:15:18.142 --> 01:15:21.270
The decryption team at the VLA
has been working around the clock...

01:15:21.437 --> 01:15:24.147
...and the hard work has finally paid off.

01:15:24.315 --> 01:15:28.277
This key section, uncovered tonight
and obtained exclusively by CNN...

01:15:28.444 --> 01:15:31.071
...shows an illustration
of what is of a human figure...

01:15:31.239 --> 01:15:34.074
...inside a geometric structure
of some kind.

01:15:34.242 --> 01:15:36.076
This and other contextual clues...

01:15:36.244 --> 01:15:39.329
...now lead scientists to believe
that the message is, in fact...

01:15:39.497 --> 01:15:43.041
- President called an emergency meeting.
- Yeah, I imagine he would.

01:15:43.209 --> 01:15:46.336
- Designed to take
a single human occupant into space...

01:15:46.504 --> 01:15:49.172
...presumably to the star Vega.

01:16:07.692 --> 01:16:09.651
MAN: I'm gonna miss
my mother's birthday party.

01:16:09.819 --> 01:16:12.696
KITZ: Call her in the morning,
tell her why you didn't show up.

01:16:12.864 --> 01:16:14.364
Tell me.

01:16:14.532 --> 01:16:15.657
They're gonna build it.

01:16:15.825 --> 01:16:16.867
Who gets to go?

01:16:17.035 --> 01:16:20.370
The president's just gone international
to spread the risk and cost...

01:16:20.538 --> 01:16:22.080
Who gets to go, though?

01:16:22.248 --> 01:16:23.874
Well, it's complicated, Ellie.

01:16:24.792 --> 01:16:25.834
What?

01:16:26.002 --> 01:16:28.837
They have formed a group
of international candidates.

01:16:29.005 --> 01:16:31.048
Now, it's your discovery.

01:16:31.466 --> 01:16:35.344
Okay, they understand that.
You're at the top of a very short list.

01:16:35.511 --> 01:16:38.055
But they're also putting together
a selection committee.

01:16:38.222 --> 01:16:42.391
It's made of scholars, theologians,
scientists, philosophers...

01:16:42.559 --> 01:16:43.559
You're on it.

01:16:44.770 --> 01:16:46.062
I've been asked, yes.

01:16:49.024 --> 01:16:50.691
I guess that means...

01:16:51.276 --> 01:16:54.028
...that you're a selector,
I'm a selectee and we can't...

01:16:54.196 --> 01:16:55.529
Yeah.

01:16:55.697 --> 01:16:58.115
What you don't understand, Ellie, is...

01:16:58.283 --> 01:17:00.409
- I understand.
- Ellie...

01:17:01.036 --> 01:17:05.373
I want you to know, whatever happens,
as far as I'm concerned...

01:17:05.957 --> 01:17:07.458
Well...

01:17:08.627 --> 01:17:10.211
...good luck.

01:17:14.216 --> 01:17:17.677
Well, whatever you do, make sure
he doesn't monopolize the committee.

01:17:17.844 --> 01:17:19.929
He is not on the committee, Ellie.

01:17:21.682 --> 01:17:23.099
What?

01:17:23.892 --> 01:17:26.936
He just resigned as science advisor.
He wants to be the one to go.

01:17:29.147 --> 01:17:32.441
MAN [ON TV]: The president is already
beginning to feel the financial pinch.

01:17:32.734 --> 01:17:34.819
Sources say the cost of the project...

01:17:34.986 --> 01:17:38.614
...is spiraling
to more than a third of a trillion dollars...

01:17:38.782 --> 01:17:42.368
...making this what may be
the most expensive single project...

01:17:42.577 --> 01:17:44.453
...in all of human history.

01:17:44.663 --> 01:17:47.998
Meanwhile, months of debate finally
reached a conclusion last week...

01:17:48.166 --> 01:17:51.293
...as 10 candidates
were selected by the IMC...

01:17:51.461 --> 01:17:55.423
...representing a cross section of
political, philosophical and religious views.

01:17:55.632 --> 01:17:58.509
Many of these are the same experts
who have been consulting...

01:17:58.677 --> 01:18:00.720
...on the Machine's design and function.

01:18:00.929 --> 01:18:05.140
They will be actively participating on-site
during the construction process.

01:18:05.307 --> 01:18:08.643
But the choice of these 10 candidates
has not been without controversy.

01:18:08.811 --> 01:18:11.646
Fully one-third of the candidates
are American.

01:18:11.814 --> 01:18:14.566
Many international observers
are asking why.

01:18:14.734 --> 01:18:17.861
The U.S. Is shouldering an
enormous percentage of the financial...

01:18:18.070 --> 01:18:21.030
Isn't it true that the contractors,
like Hadden Industries...

01:18:21.240 --> 01:18:24.576
...are making those contributions
in exchange for technology rights?

01:18:24.785 --> 01:18:28.288
Different nations are being compensated
in different ways. For example...

01:18:28.456 --> 01:18:33.001
Japan made headlines when it announced it
would forego candidate representation...

01:18:33.169 --> 01:18:36.379
...in exchange for the systems integration
subcontract.

01:18:36.547 --> 01:18:41.509
On what basis do you choose
a human being to represent humanity?

01:18:41.719 --> 01:18:42.927
Good question, Larry.

01:18:43.095 --> 01:18:45.054
Yes, well, if nothing else...

01:18:45.222 --> 01:18:49.225
...it should be somebody who is fluent in
the language the message was given in.

01:18:49.393 --> 01:18:50.602
Science, in this case.

01:18:51.228 --> 01:18:53.646
Doctor Arroway,
despite your obvious enthusiasm...

01:18:53.856 --> 01:18:56.065
...there's been a lot of criticism of late...

01:18:56.317 --> 01:18:58.818
...that this whole endeavor
is simply too dangerous.

01:18:58.986 --> 01:19:01.571
Some of that criticism from scientists.

01:19:01.781 --> 01:19:04.574
One Nobel Prize winner recently noted,
his words:

01:19:05.367 --> 01:19:07.076
"There is every indication...

01:19:07.286 --> 01:19:11.080
...that this is simply beyond our capabilities,
that this endeavor will fail...

01:19:11.290 --> 01:19:14.918
...and that the Machine's occupant
will pay for that failure with their life."

01:19:15.085 --> 01:19:16.753
How do you respond to that?

01:19:16.962 --> 01:19:20.340
ELLIE: Well, this message is from
a civilization that may be anywhere...

01:19:20.549 --> 01:19:24.260
...from hundreds to millions
and millions of years ahead of us.

01:19:24.512 --> 01:19:27.679
I have to believe that
an intelligence that advanced...

01:19:28.306 --> 01:19:30.307
...knows what they're doing.

01:19:31.226 --> 01:19:35.187
Now all it requires on our part is...

01:19:35.355 --> 01:19:36.396
Faith?

01:19:39.484 --> 01:19:41.568
I was gonna say a sense of adventure.

01:19:41.778 --> 01:19:42.986
MAN:
And in breaking news...

01:19:43.571 --> 01:19:44.863
...a former astronaut...

01:19:45.073 --> 01:19:48.909
...considered to be the leading American
candidate for the Machine seat...

01:19:49.118 --> 01:19:51.411
...has unexpectedly dropped out
of the running.

01:19:51.830 --> 01:19:54.915
Russell met with reporters this afternoon
at his Houston home.

01:19:55.250 --> 01:19:59.211
I told my dad
that I didn't want him to go.

01:19:59.420 --> 01:20:01.129
Daddy, don't go.

01:20:03.800 --> 01:20:06.885
Nothing would give me more pride
than to...

01:20:07.554 --> 01:20:09.555
...represent my country.

01:20:09.722 --> 01:20:11.932
But what can I say to this?

01:20:12.517 --> 01:20:16.353
Consortium officials had no comment,
but sources within the delegation...

01:20:16.521 --> 01:20:18.522
...have disclosed that Dr. Arroway...

01:20:18.690 --> 01:20:22.776
...appears to now be the front-runner
for the Machine seat.

01:20:23.611 --> 01:20:25.988
ELLIE:
"Meet me at noon. Must talk."

01:20:26.155 --> 01:20:28.907
I didn't expect to be getting
a message like this from you.

01:20:29.075 --> 01:20:30.284
Thanks for coming.

01:20:30.493 --> 01:20:33.453
So is this kosher?
Fraternizing with the enemy?

01:20:33.621 --> 01:20:37.124
Selectors and selectees mingling around?

01:20:37.292 --> 01:20:39.459
Can we talk about Einstein?

01:20:39.627 --> 01:20:41.795
Yeah, sure. Okay.

01:20:41.963 --> 01:20:43.380
- Special relativity.
- Yeah.

01:20:43.548 --> 01:20:45.173
This machine...

01:20:45.758 --> 01:20:50.678
...now, if it works, and you travel to Vega
at even close to the speed of light...

01:20:50.846 --> 01:20:53.347
...when you come back...
- If you come back.

01:20:55.517 --> 01:20:57.518
If you come back...

01:20:57.686 --> 01:21:01.981
...you'll only be 4 years older, but over
50 years would have passed here on Earth.

01:21:02.149 --> 01:21:03.858
Basically, yeah.

01:21:04.359 --> 01:21:06.944
And everybody that you care about...

01:21:07.821 --> 01:21:10.156
...will be gone, dead and buried.

01:21:10.991 --> 01:21:14.994
If you came back,
if you survived at all, which...

01:21:16.330 --> 01:21:20.041
Look, Palmer, nobody's saying
this isn't dangerous, all right?

01:21:20.208 --> 01:21:24.337
The rest of the candidates and myself,
we fully understand the risks we're taking.

01:21:24.504 --> 01:21:25.755
Why?

01:21:25.923 --> 01:21:28.633
Because it's a historic opportunity.
The world needs...

01:21:28.842 --> 01:21:31.469
No, you, Ellie. You. You personally.

01:21:32.512 --> 01:21:35.306
By doing this,
you're willing to give your life.

01:21:35.515 --> 01:21:37.683
You're willing to die for it.

01:21:39.519 --> 01:21:40.811
Why?

01:21:44.524 --> 01:21:48.235
From as long as I can remember,
I've been searching for...

01:21:48.862 --> 01:21:50.529
...something...

01:21:50.739 --> 01:21:54.533
...some reason why we're here.
What are we doing here? Who are we?

01:21:55.535 --> 01:21:59.413
If this is a chance to find out
even just a little part of that answer...

01:22:00.916 --> 01:22:03.918
I don't know,
I think it's won'th a human life.

01:22:04.586 --> 01:22:06.128
Don't you?

01:22:12.636 --> 01:22:15.261
You're an incredibly brave woman, Ellie.

01:22:18.057 --> 01:22:20.183
Or incredibly nuts.

01:22:42.248 --> 01:22:43.748
Palmer...

01:22:49.463 --> 01:22:51.548
I'm really confused.

01:22:52.842 --> 01:22:54.092
So am I.

01:22:55.344 --> 01:22:58.930
I think I speak for us all
when I thank you for your patience.

01:22:59.140 --> 01:23:02.600
Myself, I have one final question,
Dr. Arroway.

01:23:04.103 --> 01:23:06.438
If you should meet these Vegans...

01:23:06.647 --> 01:23:10.942
...and were permitted only
one question to ask of them...

01:23:11.110 --> 01:23:12.777
...what would it be?

01:23:14.238 --> 01:23:16.281
Well, I suppose it would be:

01:23:16.449 --> 01:23:18.116
"How did you do it?

01:23:18.659 --> 01:23:23.121
How did you evolve? How did you
survive this technological adolescence...

01:23:23.289 --> 01:23:25.206
...without destroying yourself?"

01:23:25.958 --> 01:23:30.837
That more than any other question is one
I personally would like to have answered.

01:23:31.172 --> 01:23:33.006
Not too bad, Mike.

01:23:33.674 --> 01:23:34.966
PATEL:
I join Dr. Bergeron...

01:23:35.134 --> 01:23:38.594
...in expressing thanks for
your patience, Dr. Arroway.

01:23:38.803 --> 01:23:41.305
We've all been most impressed
with your candor...

01:23:41.473 --> 01:23:43.515
...and your stamina.

01:23:43.683 --> 01:23:46.852
I believe we are ready to move on
to your final statement.

01:23:47.020 --> 01:23:48.937
Madam Chairman,
I have one more question.

01:23:49.105 --> 01:23:50.856
Yes, Mr. Joss.

01:23:51.483 --> 01:23:53.484
Dr. Arroway...

01:23:54.861 --> 01:23:57.196
Would you consider yourself...

01:23:57.697 --> 01:24:00.324
...a spiritual person?

01:24:02.994 --> 01:24:04.745
Uh...

01:24:05.497 --> 01:24:08.832
I don't really understand
the point of the question.

01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:11.877
I consider myself a moral person.

01:24:12.045 --> 01:24:14.004
PATEL:
I'm sure we all agree that is the case...

01:24:14.172 --> 01:24:16.673
...but I think what Mr. Joss
is in fact asking...

01:24:16.841 --> 01:24:18.675
Do you believe in God...

01:24:20.678 --> 01:24:22.679
...Dr. Arroway?

01:24:27.185 --> 01:24:29.603
As a scientist...

01:24:29.771 --> 01:24:33.232
...I rely on empirical evidence,
and in this matter...

01:24:33.399 --> 01:24:37.111
...I don't believe
that there is data either way.

01:24:37.695 --> 01:24:42.116
PATEL: So your answer would in fact be
that you don't believe in God.

01:24:45.537 --> 01:24:48.580
I don't understand the relevance
of the question.

01:24:49.290 --> 01:24:54.419
Dr. Arroway,
95 percent of the world's population...

01:24:54.587 --> 01:24:58.549
...believes in a supreme being
in one form or another.

01:24:59.717 --> 01:25:02.927
I believe that makes the question
more than relevant.

01:25:05.597 --> 01:25:07.306
PATEL:
Dr. Arroway?

01:25:17.234 --> 01:25:19.235
I believe, um...

01:25:23.240 --> 01:25:25.741
I believe I've already
answered that question.

01:25:29.788 --> 01:25:33.291
I'm proud of what
we've achieved as a species...

01:25:33.458 --> 01:25:35.459
...and as a civilization.

01:25:37.129 --> 01:25:39.630
I would hate to see
everything we stand for...

01:25:39.798 --> 01:25:43.718
...all that we have fought for
for a thousand generations...

01:25:43.927 --> 01:25:46.262
...all that God has blessed us with...

01:25:47.598 --> 01:25:49.140
...betrayed...

01:25:50.100 --> 01:25:54.687
...in the final hour because we chose to
send a representative who did not put our...

01:25:55.189 --> 01:25:57.982
...most cherished beliefs first.

01:26:01.278 --> 01:26:02.445
Thank you.

01:26:08.619 --> 01:26:10.953
[KNOCKING]

01:26:35.686 --> 01:26:36.978
Why did you do it?

01:26:41.567 --> 01:26:45.737
Our job was to select someone
to speak for everybody.

01:26:49.033 --> 01:26:52.494
I just couldn't in good conscience
vote for a person...

01:26:52.662 --> 01:26:54.663
...who doesn't believe in God.

01:26:56.707 --> 01:26:58.083
Someone who...

01:26:58.251 --> 01:27:01.670
...honestly thinks
the other 95 percent of us...

01:27:01.879 --> 01:27:04.839
...suffer from some form
of mass delusion.

01:27:08.010 --> 01:27:10.095
I told the truth up there.

01:27:11.389 --> 01:27:14.891
And Drumlin told you exactly
what you wanted to hear.

01:27:50.051 --> 01:27:52.636
DRUMLIN:
With full humility and utmost gratitude...

01:27:52.804 --> 01:27:55.014
...I accept this great honor...

01:27:55.223 --> 01:27:59.268
...and I promise I will do my best
to represent my nation...

01:27:59.436 --> 01:28:04.565
...my planet and my God
on this historic journey.

01:28:04.733 --> 01:28:07.067
I thank you from the bottom of my heart.

01:28:07.235 --> 01:28:10.195
[APPLAUDING]

01:28:49.652 --> 01:28:52.613
MAN [ON TV]: There's
a carnival atmosphere at Cape Canaveral...

01:28:52.781 --> 01:28:54.823
...as the International
Machine Consortium...

01:28:54.991 --> 01:28:58.452
...hosts as much a media event
as a systems test.

01:28:58.953 --> 01:29:02.623
David Drumlin is supervising
the on-site portion of the test.

01:29:02.832 --> 01:29:04.625
We spoke with him earlier today.

01:29:04.793 --> 01:29:07.294
DRUMLIN: We'll be able to monjtor
the stresses and effects...

01:29:07.462 --> 01:29:09.797
...using the robot passenger...

01:29:10.298 --> 01:29:12.591
...who we lovingly call Elmer.

01:29:12.758 --> 01:29:15.885
WOMAN [OVER SPEAKER]: We are coming up
on T-minus two hours and counting.

01:29:16.053 --> 01:29:18.096
All Machine systems are go.

01:29:18.263 --> 01:29:21.140
Dr. Arroway, the press would like to
ask you a few questions...

01:29:21.308 --> 01:29:23.976
...as soon as they're done
with Dr. Drumlin.

01:29:25.270 --> 01:29:27.522
DRUMLIN: Now, at the moment
where we release the pod...

01:29:27.689 --> 01:29:31.275
...there will be a substantial
amount of energy generated at the core.

01:29:31.777 --> 01:29:34.153
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

01:29:34.321 --> 01:29:38.491
...using our robot passenger,
who we lovingly call Elmer.

01:29:38.659 --> 01:29:39.826
[CHUCKLES]

01:29:39.993 --> 01:29:41.619
- Thank you.
- Welcome.

01:29:41.787 --> 01:29:43.704
WOMAN:
- The test area is clear and go.

01:29:43.872 --> 01:29:46.666
Sir, they're ready for you out at the site.

01:29:46.834 --> 01:29:48.459
Yeah, just a minute.

01:29:49.503 --> 01:29:52.797
WOMAN: The test director has issued a go
to enter the final countdown phase.

01:29:52.965 --> 01:29:54.298
Ellie.

01:29:54.466 --> 01:29:56.843
- Congratulations, David.
- Glad you could come.

01:29:58.178 --> 01:30:00.638
Didrt, uh, expect to see you here.

01:30:01.348 --> 01:30:06.185
Well, I'm still, you know,
Crew Ops at the Control Center.

01:30:06.854 --> 01:30:10.857
And I suppose the fact that I discovered
the message means that I have PR value.

01:30:11.024 --> 01:30:12.692
Of course.

01:30:14.194 --> 01:30:17.363
Ellie, I know you must think
this is all very unfair.

01:30:18.031 --> 01:30:20.324
And maybe that's an understatement.

01:30:21.410 --> 01:30:23.786
What you don't know is, I agree.

01:30:24.371 --> 01:30:27.665
I wish the world was a place
where fair was the bottom line.

01:30:27.833 --> 01:30:31.043
Where the kind of idealism you showed
at the hearing was rewarded...

01:30:31.211 --> 01:30:33.504
...not taken advantage of.

01:30:35.215 --> 01:30:38.341
Unfortunately,
we don't live in that world.

01:30:40.386 --> 01:30:41.887
Funny...

01:30:42.930 --> 01:30:46.391
...I always believed that the world
is what we make of it.

01:30:48.060 --> 01:30:51.229
Excuse me, Dr. Drumlin, sir?

01:30:52.857 --> 01:30:54.399
Good luck on the test.

01:30:54.650 --> 01:30:56.985
- The pad leader has issued the order...
- Thank you.

01:30:57.153 --> 01:31:00.322
...to clear the pad of all nonessential...
- Right this way, sir.

01:31:04.827 --> 01:31:08.705
Test director, everything looks good
up here. We're ready to go.

01:31:08.873 --> 01:31:11.875
STEVE: All right, people, I want
things double and triple checked here.

01:31:12.043 --> 01:31:15.629
We only get one shot at this.
Let's get it right.

01:31:15.796 --> 01:31:18.882
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are ready for startup.

01:31:19.091 --> 01:31:22.427
All controllers, I need a go-no-go
for test initiation.

01:31:22.595 --> 01:31:23.595
- Mechanical?
MAN 1: Go.

01:31:23.763 --> 01:31:24.804
- Electrical?
MAN 2: Go.

01:31:24.972 --> 01:31:26.056
- Dynamics?
MAN 3: Go.

01:31:26.224 --> 01:31:27.516
- Communications?
MAN 4: Go.

01:31:27.683 --> 01:31:28.725
- Pod systems?
WOMAN: Go

01:31:28.893 --> 01:31:30.435
- Safety?
MAN 5: Go.

01:31:30.603 --> 01:31:33.522
Crew Ops, verify all pre-test
procedures are complete.

01:31:33.689 --> 01:31:35.106
Yes, verified. I'm go.

01:31:35.274 --> 01:31:37.776
Pad leader, we are good.
Is everything okay with you?

01:31:37.944 --> 01:31:40.612
Roger. The pad is a go.

01:31:40.780 --> 01:31:43.615
STEVE:
Test initiation, on my mark.

01:31:44.075 --> 01:31:45.450
Five...

01:31:45.618 --> 01:31:46.868
...four...

01:31:47.036 --> 01:31:48.328
...three...

01:31:48.496 --> 01:31:49.704
...two...

01:31:50.122 --> 01:31:51.623
...one.

01:31:51.791 --> 01:31:53.208
Mark.

01:31:53.376 --> 01:31:55.126
MAN 1: Test start.
MAN 2: Rings are unlocked.

01:31:55.294 --> 01:31:57.045
MAN 3:
Power levels indicate a good start.

01:31:57.213 --> 01:32:00.089
WOMAN 1: We have begun the full-scale
test of Earth's first system...

01:32:00.257 --> 01:32:03.801
...built by the sharing of knowledge
with a neighbor in our universe.

01:32:03.969 --> 01:32:06.220
MAN 4:
All power sources on core induction bus.

01:32:06.388 --> 01:32:08.013
WOMAN 2:
IPV power transfer.

01:32:08.181 --> 01:32:11.934
GERRY: Ring motion detect.
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

01:32:12.978 --> 01:32:16.021
STEVE: Gerry, how are we looking?
GERRY: Looks good. We're underway.

01:32:16.189 --> 01:32:17.940
DRUMLIN:
Looks like we have a normal startup.

01:32:18.108 --> 01:32:20.651
STEVE:
Roger, David. It's looking good here.

01:32:20.819 --> 01:32:23.070
[CHEERING]

01:32:26.283 --> 01:32:29.410
WOMAN 1: We are moments away from
the initiation of the drop sequence.

01:32:29.578 --> 01:32:31.579
All systems are go.

01:32:33.707 --> 01:32:36.333
STEVE: Mechanical, you still happy?
MAN 1: Roger that.

01:32:36.501 --> 01:32:39.962
DRUMLIN: I'll tell you, this is very exciting
from up here.

01:32:42.132 --> 01:32:45.759
GERRY: We've got 4 percent.
DRUMLIN: We're confirming 4 percent.

01:32:47.012 --> 01:32:50.347
Frequency 9.85.

01:32:50.515 --> 01:32:56.270
Harmonics in the green. G-level 1.1.

01:32:56.438 --> 01:32:59.773
- Five percent.
- Confirmed. We are at 5 percent.

01:32:59.941 --> 01:33:01.692
David, how's it looking to you?

01:33:01.860 --> 01:33:04.695
DRUMLIN: Okay. I'm gonna take a look
and show you what we got.

01:33:04.863 --> 01:33:07.031
MAN 2: All test-subject instrumentation
looks good.

01:33:07.198 --> 01:33:10.868
Confirmed, we have a good picture
from Dr. Drumlirs PRD.

01:33:11.036 --> 01:33:13.495
DRUMLIN: Hope you guys are seeing
what I'm seeing.

01:33:13.872 --> 01:33:15.789
MAN 3:
All systems are go.

01:33:17.375 --> 01:33:18.959
DRUMLIN:
This is really something.

01:33:19.169 --> 01:33:20.836
MAN 4:
For purposes of this test...

01:33:21.004 --> 01:33:25.214
...Dr. Drumlin will be on top of
the gantry crane that's over the Machine.

01:33:25.382 --> 01:33:27.550
We've got some video animation...

01:33:27.718 --> 01:33:31.220
...to show you just how this machine,
it is thought, will work.

01:33:31.388 --> 01:33:33.056
The passenger pod will be released.

01:33:33.265 --> 01:33:37.602
It will come down through the center of
the rings and into the Machine's core.

01:33:37.770 --> 01:33:41.856
The big question everyone here is asking is,
of course, what happens then?

01:33:42.024 --> 01:33:46.861
Some believe that the rings function as
some sort of an accelerator or something...

01:33:47.029 --> 01:33:49.656
...sending its energy
into this passenger pod...

01:33:49.823 --> 01:33:52.533
...making it rocket away
at near the speed of light.

01:33:52.743 --> 01:33:57.372
Other people believe it might open up
a doorway to some other dimension.

01:33:57.539 --> 01:34:01.000
Who's right?
Well, that's what today's test is all about.

01:34:01.627 --> 01:34:04.087
GERRY: Thirty-five percent.
MAN 1: Subsystems, are you ready?

01:34:04.254 --> 01:34:07.423
GERRY: Forty percent normal acceleration.
MAN 2: Roger, confirm 40 percent.

01:34:07.633 --> 01:34:10.593
STEVE: All controllers stand by
to initiate drop sequence...

01:34:10.761 --> 01:34:12.345
...on my mark.

01:34:12.513 --> 01:34:14.847
MAN 3:
All systems ready for drop sequence.

01:34:15.015 --> 01:34:17.266
GERRY:
Forty-five percent.

01:34:17.434 --> 01:34:19.602
DRUMLIN:
We're reading 45 percent.

01:34:20.604 --> 01:34:22.605
Can you verify closure?

01:34:23.899 --> 01:34:25.441
GERRY:
Forty-six.

01:34:25.609 --> 01:34:30.279
STEVE: All controllers stand by
to initiate IPV drop sequence. On my mark.

01:34:30.948 --> 01:34:32.699
GERRY:
Forty-eight percent.

01:34:33.325 --> 01:34:35.743
DRUMLIN: Test djrector,
I'm feeling a very strange vibration.

01:34:35.911 --> 01:34:37.120
Are you feeling it down there?

01:34:37.287 --> 01:34:39.247
STEVE:
Gerry, can you confirm any vibration?

01:34:39.790 --> 01:34:41.624
GERRY:
Negative, everything looks good here.

01:34:41.792 --> 01:34:43.793
- Crew Ops?
- Nothing wrong with Elmer.

01:34:43.961 --> 01:34:45.795
We're not seeing anything abnormal.

01:34:45.963 --> 01:34:48.755
DRUMLIN: No good. Hold the sequence.
I'm gonna take a direct reading.

01:34:49.257 --> 01:34:52.634
STEVE: What the hell is he talking about?
- Can anyone say grandstanding?

01:34:52.802 --> 01:34:54.803
He sure knows he's on TV!

01:34:54.971 --> 01:34:58.098
Back home that's what we call
an overcooked ham.

01:34:58.266 --> 01:35:00.767
DRUMLIN:
I'm reading 10 kilohertz!

01:35:00.935 --> 01:35:03.729
What's your reading on the first
and second order G-levels?

01:35:03.938 --> 01:35:05.814
MAN 1:
G-levels are right on.

01:35:06.315 --> 01:35:09.818
MAN 2: We confirm Drumlirs readings
and they're all normal. We're go.

01:35:09.986 --> 01:35:11.486
STEVE:
Copy that, Dynamics.

01:35:11.654 --> 01:35:14.406
I think we're okay,
but we'll let him finish.

01:35:15.616 --> 01:35:17.659
- Mechanical, you still okay?
MAN 3: Roger, chief.

01:35:17.827 --> 01:35:19.161
We're right on the money.

01:35:19.328 --> 01:35:21.621
We've got a security problem here.

01:35:21.789 --> 01:35:23.373
Ellie, are you sure?

01:35:23.541 --> 01:35:25.834
Yeah. This guy, he shouldn't be there.
I know him.

01:35:26.002 --> 01:35:28.962
Gerry, execute the
rapid shutdown sequence.

01:35:29.130 --> 01:35:32.424
Security, move emergency
response team into position one.

01:35:32.592 --> 01:35:35.177
- Get me Drumlin on a secure loop, please.
- You got him.

01:35:35.344 --> 01:35:38.847
- David, can you hear me?
DRUMLIN: Yes, I hear.

01:35:39.015 --> 01:35:41.308
ELLIE: All right, we've got
a security breach here.

01:35:41.684 --> 01:35:43.685
Right behind you. The tall guy.

01:35:44.187 --> 01:35:47.439
The technician. See him?

01:35:49.484 --> 01:35:51.860
He's not supposed to be there.

01:35:56.532 --> 01:35:59.201
David, he's got something in his hand!

01:35:59.368 --> 01:36:01.912
Him! Take him! Security breach!

01:36:02.580 --> 01:36:03.705
He's got a bomb!

01:36:03.873 --> 01:36:06.500
STEVE: I want that emergency-response
team up on the gantry now.

01:36:06.667 --> 01:36:08.335
Security, stage one alert.

01:36:08.503 --> 01:36:13.005
By God, move all the fire and
rescue personnel into position one.

01:36:13.840 --> 01:36:15.674
[YELLING]

01:36:29.022 --> 01:36:31.565
[SCREAMING]

01:36:49.584 --> 01:36:51.710
STEVE:
All right, all right, back to your stations.

01:36:51.878 --> 01:36:55.005
I need you to be professional, people.
Settle down.

01:36:55.215 --> 01:36:58.092
Pad leader, pad leader, do you copy?

01:37:15.527 --> 01:37:18.195
The scene earlier today,
when David Drumlin...

01:37:18.405 --> 01:37:20.114
...advisor to two presidents...

01:37:20.282 --> 01:37:24.285
...and winner of the National Academy
of Sciences lifetime award...

01:37:24.452 --> 01:37:28.247
...was laid to rest
at Arlington National Cemetery.

01:37:31.960 --> 01:37:33.878
In a related story, last night's raid...

01:37:34.045 --> 01:37:35.587
Can I help you?

01:37:35.754 --> 01:37:39.799
- Oh, you're... I've got some mail for you.
...resulted in the discovery of this video.

01:37:39.967 --> 01:37:44.679
The suicide note of the leader of the
terrorist group now believed responsible...

01:37:44.847 --> 01:37:47.390
...for the explosion in Florida this week.

01:37:47.558 --> 01:37:52.562
What we do,
we do for the goodness of all mankind.

01:37:53.230 --> 01:37:56.149
This won't be understood, not now...

01:37:56.317 --> 01:37:58.276
...but the apocalypse to come...

01:37:59.445 --> 01:38:01.613
...will vindicate our faith.

01:38:10.748 --> 01:38:14.459
[PULSING]

01:38:25.930 --> 01:38:27.764
Welcome home.

01:39:23.361 --> 01:39:25.654
[MAN SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN
ON TV]

01:39:33.538 --> 01:39:35.914
Oh, Comrade Arroway...

01:39:36.082 --> 01:39:39.376
...he has been expecting your call.
One moment, please.

01:39:49.137 --> 01:39:50.345
Mr. Hadden?

01:39:50.972 --> 01:39:52.305
Doctor.

01:39:53.433 --> 01:39:55.225
How kind of you to call.

01:39:55.935 --> 01:39:58.353
Mr. Hadden, where are you?

01:40:00.064 --> 01:40:04.735
The Russian government was kind enough
to give me accommodations on Mir.

01:40:05.570 --> 01:40:07.446
You're living on a space station?

01:40:08.948 --> 01:40:11.283
It's quite simple, really.

01:40:12.326 --> 01:40:15.912
The low-oxygen,
zero-gravity environment...

01:40:16.080 --> 01:40:20.792
...is the only thing keeping
the cancer from eating me alive.

01:40:22.335 --> 01:40:25.046
Actually, I quite like it up here.

01:40:25.505 --> 01:40:29.300
My little room has one hell of a view.

01:40:36.475 --> 01:40:38.976
I wanna show you something.

01:40:43.148 --> 01:40:45.608
Hokkaido Island.

01:40:46.526 --> 01:40:48.903
The systems integration site.

01:40:49.905 --> 01:40:52.156
Look closer.

01:40:59.790 --> 01:41:03.417
First rule in government spending:

01:41:03.585 --> 01:41:07.505
Why build one when you can have
two at twice the price?

01:41:07.672 --> 01:41:11.467
Only, this one can be kept secret.

01:41:11.635 --> 01:41:13.677
Controlled by Americans...

01:41:13.845 --> 01:41:17.473
...built by the Japanese subcontractors...

01:41:18.183 --> 01:41:21.769
...who also happen to be...

01:41:21.937 --> 01:41:24.021
...recently acquired...

01:41:24.189 --> 01:41:27.316
...wholly-owned subsidiaries...

01:41:27.484 --> 01:41:29.860
...of Hadden Industries.
- Of Hadden Industries.

01:41:33.031 --> 01:41:36.200
They still want
an American to go, doctor.

01:41:39.830 --> 01:41:42.164
Wanna take a ride?

01:42:24.290 --> 01:42:28.585
WOMAN: And augmenting our restraint and
communications console subsystem...

01:42:28.752 --> 01:42:30.753
...we have your personal recording unit.

01:42:30.921 --> 01:42:35.049
Normal, infrared and ultraviolet lenses.

01:42:35.217 --> 01:42:39.262
Digital microchip good for
thousands of hours of recording.

01:42:40.472 --> 01:42:42.557
Okay, look, I understand...

01:42:42.725 --> 01:42:46.144
...the reason for recording
and documenting the mission.

01:42:46.312 --> 01:42:49.147
But I just... I wanna go on record
one more time.

01:42:49.315 --> 01:42:52.817
The transmitted specs
never said anything about any chair...

01:42:53.068 --> 01:42:57.572
...or a restraining harness or survival gear.

01:42:57.740 --> 01:42:59.574
Why can't we just trust the original...?

01:42:59.742 --> 01:43:03.870
Doctor, both the IMC Board
and the SI team reviewed the matter...

01:43:04.079 --> 01:43:07.832
...and concluded that
the design impact is negligible.

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:09.708
Bottom line is...

01:43:09.876 --> 01:43:12.211
...we're not putting anybody
aboard this machine...

01:43:12.420 --> 01:43:15.422
...unless there is
some sort of minimal protection.

01:43:15.590 --> 01:43:17.466
End of story.

01:43:19.886 --> 01:43:23.138
- Okay.
MAN: Ellie...

01:43:24.015 --> 01:43:28.101
...we've been giving these to the astronauts
since the beginning of the space program.

01:43:29.437 --> 01:43:31.730
It's never been made public, of course.

01:43:31.940 --> 01:43:34.024
It's fast and it's painless.

01:43:36.778 --> 01:43:39.655
I'm gonna travel 26 light years
to commit suicide?

01:43:39.822 --> 01:43:42.032
Something may go wrong.

01:43:42.200 --> 01:43:44.952
There may be
an unforeseen mechanical failure.

01:43:45.703 --> 01:43:48.789
You could be marooned, unable to return.

01:43:49.958 --> 01:43:53.085
There are a thousand reasons
we can think of for you to have this...

01:43:53.294 --> 01:43:56.463
...but mostly it's for the reasons
we can't think of.

01:44:21.531 --> 01:44:22.572
[KNOCKING]

01:44:22.740 --> 01:44:23.865
Come in.

01:44:25.410 --> 01:44:29.413
- Dr. Arroway, time to get ready.
- Thank you.

01:44:40.090 --> 01:44:41.799
I know you don't have much time.

01:44:41.967 --> 01:44:45.052
As soon as I found out about the Machine,
I called the president.

01:44:45.262 --> 01:44:47.346
I came with Kitz.

01:44:47.514 --> 01:44:49.807
I had to see you one more time.

01:44:49.975 --> 01:44:51.726
- Oh, God, I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

01:44:51.893 --> 01:44:53.769
No, I'm glad you came.

01:44:53.937 --> 01:44:56.814
There's something I gotta say to you.

01:44:57.691 --> 01:45:01.944
The reason I didn't vote for you to go was
a good reason, but it wasrt the real one.

01:45:03.030 --> 01:45:05.031
I didn't vote for you to go...

01:45:06.575 --> 01:45:08.743
...because I don't wanna lose you.

01:45:09.786 --> 01:45:12.621
You find your way home, all right?

01:45:29.014 --> 01:45:30.431
Twenty-three hours ago...

01:45:30.599 --> 01:45:34.643
...the world was stunned by the
announcement of a second Machine...

01:45:34.811 --> 01:45:37.938
...and its passenger,
Eleanor Ann Arroway.

01:45:38.148 --> 01:45:41.734
Now the question
that's on everyone's mind:

01:45:41.902 --> 01:45:43.903
Will history repeat itself?

01:45:44.071 --> 01:45:46.364
With a piece of engineering
this complex...

01:45:46.531 --> 01:45:50.618
...with so many unknowns,
could the unthinkable occur?

01:45:50.786 --> 01:45:54.246
The security in Hokkaido
has been incredibly tight.

01:45:54.414 --> 01:45:57.749
No reporters whatsoever
have been allowed near the site.

01:48:19.724 --> 01:48:21.725
Thanks.

01:48:38.284 --> 01:48:41.286
Magnetic restraint is secure.
All life support functions normal.

01:48:41.496 --> 01:48:44.664
Roger that. Ellie, this is Control.
Do you copy?

01:48:44.831 --> 01:48:47.166
Ellie to Control, reading you five-by-five.

01:48:47.334 --> 01:48:51.420
- Comm 1, Give me Ellie's PRD.
- Video unit recording and transmitting.

01:48:52.381 --> 01:48:54.924
- Are you reading me?
STEVE: That's affirmative.

01:48:55.092 --> 01:48:57.385
Video looks good.

01:48:57.553 --> 01:49:00.096
- Copy that, Control.
- Okay.

01:49:00.264 --> 01:49:03.140
Ellie, we're gonna proceed
to button you up.

01:49:03.308 --> 01:49:05.977
Roger, Control. I'm ready.

01:49:09.398 --> 01:49:11.774
- Dynamics...
- I can confirm the walkway retraction.

01:49:11.942 --> 01:49:12.942
STEVE: Systems?
MAN 1: Go.

01:49:13.110 --> 01:49:14.485
STEVE: Communications?
MAN 2: Go.

01:49:14.653 --> 01:49:16.320
STEVE: Life support?
WOMAN: Go.

01:49:16.488 --> 01:49:18.781
Ellie, we are go for closure.

01:49:20.242 --> 01:49:22.118
I'm go here.

01:49:22.995 --> 01:49:26.497
STEVE: Mechanical, initiate
IPV closure sequence.

01:49:28.125 --> 01:49:30.334
Hold on, let me get you a chair.

01:49:31.044 --> 01:49:32.086
ELLIE:
I'm go.

01:49:32.254 --> 01:49:36.132
- It's nice to smell you again, Mr. Kitz.
- You too.

01:49:36.300 --> 01:49:38.134
Wouldrt peg him as a Polo man.

01:49:47.686 --> 01:49:49.020
I got a visual on the door.

01:49:49.187 --> 01:49:51.147
WOMAN:
IPV escape system is armed.

01:49:51.315 --> 01:49:53.316
Door is looking good.

01:49:58.530 --> 01:50:00.197
Door alignment looks good.

01:50:28.809 --> 01:50:30.894
Ellie, we are showing green
across the board.

01:50:31.062 --> 01:50:34.397
Copy that, Control. IPV is secure.

01:50:41.530 --> 01:50:43.531
GERRY:
We are at 30 percent.

01:50:43.699 --> 01:50:44.991
Copy that, 30 percent.

01:50:49.872 --> 01:50:52.540
- How you doing in there, EI?
- Kent?

01:50:53.292 --> 01:50:56.086
- Is that you?
- That's a big affirmative.

01:50:57.004 --> 01:50:58.588
Who let you in there, huh?

01:50:58.756 --> 01:51:00.882
A higher power intervened.

01:51:02.927 --> 01:51:04.260
Well, I'm glad you came.

01:51:09.016 --> 01:51:10.183
GERRY:
Thirty-five percent.

01:51:10.935 --> 01:51:12.435
Copy that, 35 percent.

01:51:12.603 --> 01:51:13.937
- Mechanical?
- We're good.

01:51:14.105 --> 01:51:15.438
Forty percent.

01:51:19.068 --> 01:51:20.944
I'm picking up a moderate vibration here.

01:51:22.113 --> 01:51:25.740
- Dynamics, can you confirm vibration?
GERRY: Everything looks good here.

01:51:25.950 --> 01:51:29.202
She's feeling the same thing
they felt at the Cape at this point.

01:51:29.370 --> 01:51:30.954
Ellie, the vibration is normal.

01:51:31.122 --> 01:51:33.622
GERRY: We are at 50 percent.
All systems nominal.

01:51:33.790 --> 01:51:35.791
Copy that, 50 percent.

01:51:40.964 --> 01:51:42.965
Vibration is getting a little stronger now.

01:51:43.133 --> 01:51:45.968
We're picking up
some low-frequency noise.

01:51:46.344 --> 01:51:49.430
- Mechanical, can you confirm?
- It looks fine to me.

01:51:49.597 --> 01:51:52.975
STEVE: Roger. Gerry, what do you think?
- I'm still go.

01:51:53.143 --> 01:51:54.768
People, we are still go.

01:51:56.521 --> 01:51:58.981
What...? Something's happening.

01:52:00.233 --> 01:52:02.901
I'm... There's...

01:52:03.069 --> 01:52:05.904
There's a light. Do you see that?
I'm seeing some...

01:52:06.656 --> 01:52:09.116
Something, some...

01:52:09.284 --> 01:52:11.827
I can't tell whether it's daylight or not.

01:52:11.995 --> 01:52:14.913
There it is again.
It's coming from the bottom.

01:52:15.957 --> 01:52:17.499
Here, let me show you. See that?

01:52:17.667 --> 01:52:19.585
Negative. Ellie, you're breaking up.

01:52:19.753 --> 01:52:22.588
- Comm 1, can we boost her signal?
- Already at maximum.

01:52:22.756 --> 01:52:24.298
GERRY:
Sixty-five percent.

01:52:24.466 --> 01:52:26.175
The material is changing.

01:52:26.342 --> 01:52:29.845
It's bordering on translucence.
But the system is intact.

01:52:33.141 --> 01:52:37.519
It's gotta be some kind
of electromagnetic field.

01:52:37.687 --> 01:52:40.689
- Are you reading this?
- Negative, we're seeing only interference.

01:52:40.857 --> 01:52:46.195
It's becoming completely translucent.
I can't describe it. I can't even explain it.

01:52:48.656 --> 01:52:49.698
Seventy percent.

01:52:49.866 --> 01:52:52.201
People, we have intermittent comm,
but we are go.

01:52:52.368 --> 01:52:56.829
- Initiate secondary drive systems.
GERRY: Initiating auxiliary booster sequence.

01:52:57.039 --> 01:52:58.873
MAN:
We're go for ignition.

01:53:05.923 --> 01:53:08.382
We have auxiliary booster ignition.

01:53:14.056 --> 01:53:15.556
Life support, how is she doing?

01:53:15.724 --> 01:53:18.976
We still have data. Heart and respiration
are high but within limits.

01:53:19.144 --> 01:53:20.228
Ellie, do you copy?

01:53:20.437 --> 01:53:23.439
If you could hear, I am okay to go.

01:53:27.236 --> 01:53:29.028
If you could hear me...

01:53:32.115 --> 01:53:33.491
Eighty percent.

01:53:33.659 --> 01:53:36.494
All vibration and G-levels are in the green.

01:53:41.917 --> 01:53:44.252
Control, if you're reading me...

01:53:44.419 --> 01:53:46.754
...I am okay to go. Okay to go,

01:53:46.922 --> 01:53:50.716
GERRY: Eighty-five percent.
MAN: All bearing tips are on the profile.

01:53:51.593 --> 01:53:54.679
Ninety percent. We're detecting
some structural instability.

01:53:54.847 --> 01:53:58.766
- Confirmed. Is she holding?
- We're within limits, barely.

01:54:00.269 --> 01:54:06.190
I'm okay to go.

01:54:12.114 --> 01:54:13.573
My God!

01:54:24.625 --> 01:54:27.127
Okay to go. I'm okay.

01:54:27.545 --> 01:54:29.045
Hundred percent target velocity.

01:54:29.213 --> 01:54:30.422
MAN:
Steve?

01:54:30.590 --> 01:54:34.968
Tremendous EMI levels around the Machine.
All field measurements are off-scale.

01:54:35.136 --> 01:54:37.596
Steve, we're approaching our abort limits.

01:54:39.974 --> 01:54:41.057
Okay to go.

01:54:46.272 --> 01:54:47.480
I hear her!

01:54:47.648 --> 01:54:50.483
I hear her. Barely, but she's there.

01:54:50.651 --> 01:54:53.653
- Okay to go.
- She says she's okay to go.

01:54:56.657 --> 01:54:58.783
Steve, we're real close.

01:54:58.951 --> 01:55:01.828
- Electrical, reading in the core?
MAN: Internal environment normal.

01:55:01.996 --> 01:55:04.998
Inside the core, the weather's beautiful.

01:55:09.086 --> 01:55:10.337
I'm okay to go.

01:55:10.838 --> 01:55:14.299
Okay to go. I'm okay to go.

01:55:14.884 --> 01:55:17.218
STEVE:
Initiate drop sequence.

01:55:19.805 --> 01:55:21.514
On my mark.

01:55:22.224 --> 01:55:24.768
Ten, nine...

01:55:25.853 --> 01:55:27.854
...eight...

01:55:28.189 --> 01:55:31.191
...seven, six...

01:55:31.359 --> 01:55:33.985
...five, four...

01:55:34.153 --> 01:55:36.821
...three, two...

01:55:36.989 --> 01:55:38.365
I'm okay to go.

01:55:42.328 --> 01:55:44.119
Oh, God!

01:55:53.380 --> 01:55:55.047
Ellie to Control.

01:55:55.715 --> 01:56:05.766
Ellie to Control, do you read me?

01:56:11.523 --> 01:56:14.942
I'm gonna try to keep recording.

01:56:15.694 --> 01:56:20.239
I'm going through
some kind of a tunnel.

01:56:34.921 --> 01:56:36.463
There's a light source ahead.

01:56:36.965 --> 01:56:40.175
Brilliant and blue-white.

01:56:41.386 --> 01:56:43.012
Residual radiation?

01:56:54.774 --> 01:56:56.066
It's a star.

01:56:56.651 --> 01:57:00.070
I must have gone through a wormhole.

01:57:05.118 --> 01:57:06.535
It's Vega.

01:57:17.755 --> 01:57:19.297
I'm in another wormhole now.

01:57:22.968 --> 01:57:24.093
I had no idea.

01:57:24.261 --> 01:57:26.054
A series of them.

01:57:29.058 --> 01:57:30.308
They're alive.

01:57:30.476 --> 01:57:34.437
It's like some kind of a transit system.

01:57:35.439 --> 01:57:36.814
It's a subway.

01:57:36.982 --> 01:57:38.483
[YELLS]

01:57:42.154 --> 01:57:43.946
Okay.

01:57:44.114 --> 01:57:46.407
Okay, I've gotta keep talking.

01:57:48.952 --> 01:57:52.830
It's a triple... No, quadruple system.

01:57:53.248 --> 01:57:54.499
It's beautiful.

01:57:57.836 --> 01:57:59.253
They're alive.

01:58:07.429 --> 01:58:09.097
Another wormhole!

01:58:09.431 --> 01:58:11.265
This one is much more violent!

01:59:44.692 --> 01:59:46.359
Some...

01:59:46.819 --> 01:59:49.154
...celestial event...

01:59:50.406 --> 01:59:52.115
No...

01:59:52.283 --> 01:59:55.951
No words. No words...

01:59:57.621 --> 01:59:59.830
...to describe it.

02:00:01.249 --> 02:00:03.125
Poetry.

02:00:04.294 --> 02:00:07.796
They should have sent a poet.

02:00:08.089 --> 02:00:10.674
It's so beautiful.

02:00:10.842 --> 02:00:12.301
Beautiful.

02:00:14.137 --> 02:00:19.433
So beautiful.

02:00:20.310 --> 02:00:26.899
I had no idea.

02:00:28.151 --> 02:00:31.487
I had no...

02:00:32.781 --> 02:00:36.075
I had no idea.

02:00:37.410 --> 02:00:44.416
I had no idea. I had no idea.

02:03:02.387 --> 02:03:03.762
Hi, Sparks.

02:03:05.640 --> 02:03:07.140
Dad?

02:03:14.607 --> 02:03:16.483
I missed you.

02:03:22.115 --> 02:03:23.281
Arert you...?

02:03:23.491 --> 02:03:26.701
I'm sorry I couldn't
be there for you, sweetheart.

02:03:36.504 --> 02:03:38.171
You're not real.

02:03:39.674 --> 02:03:41.174
None of this is real.

02:03:41.342 --> 02:03:43.510
That's my scientist.

02:03:44.595 --> 02:03:48.974
When I was unconscious, you downloaded
my thoughts, my memory even.

02:03:49.809 --> 02:03:51.852
Pensacola.

02:03:54.355 --> 02:03:57.315
We thought this might
make things easier for you.

02:04:10.829 --> 02:04:14.457
- Why did you contact us?
- You contacted us.

02:04:14.624 --> 02:04:16.292
We were just listening.

02:04:17.169 --> 02:04:18.461
And there are others?

02:04:18.628 --> 02:04:20.254
Many others.

02:04:25.093 --> 02:04:26.594
They all...

02:04:26.761 --> 02:04:29.889
...travel here through that
transit system that you built?

02:04:30.432 --> 02:04:31.932
We didn't build it.

02:04:33.101 --> 02:04:34.602
We don't know who did.

02:04:36.688 --> 02:04:39.648
No, they were gone
long before we ever got here.

02:04:40.275 --> 02:04:42.109
Maybe someday they'll come back.

02:04:42.944 --> 02:04:45.654
All the other civilizations that you find,
they come here?

02:04:45.864 --> 02:04:47.072
Not all.

02:04:48.867 --> 02:04:52.036
- Is this some test?
- No, no tests.

02:04:54.956 --> 02:04:56.540
You have your mother's hands.

02:05:06.718 --> 02:05:08.886
You're an interesting species...

02:05:09.554 --> 02:05:11.514
...an interesting mix.

02:05:12.432 --> 02:05:15.226
You're capable of
such beautiful dreams...

02:05:16.269 --> 02:05:18.729
...and such horrible nightmares.

02:05:19.898 --> 02:05:21.732
You feel so lost...

02:05:22.317 --> 02:05:25.277
...so cut off, so alone.

02:05:26.738 --> 02:05:28.489
Only you're not.

02:05:30.574 --> 02:05:32.116
See...

02:05:32.576 --> 02:05:34.202
In all our searching...

02:05:34.411 --> 02:05:37.914
...the only thing we've found
that makes the emptiness bearable...

02:05:38.082 --> 02:05:39.707
...is each other.

02:05:43.462 --> 02:05:45.380
What happens now?

02:05:46.423 --> 02:05:47.924
Now?

02:05:48.842 --> 02:05:50.635
You go home.

02:05:50.803 --> 02:05:52.220
ELLIE:
Home?

02:05:52.388 --> 02:05:55.473
But I have so many questions.

02:05:55.641 --> 02:05:57.767
Do we get to come back?

02:05:58.644 --> 02:06:00.895
This was just a first step.

02:06:01.063 --> 02:06:02.814
In time, you'll take another.

02:06:04.400 --> 02:06:06.776
But other people need to see
what I've seen...

02:06:06.944 --> 02:06:09.988
This is the way it's been done
for billions of years.

02:06:11.991 --> 02:06:14.617
- But I...
- Small moves, Ellie.

02:06:16.078 --> 02:06:17.996
Small moves.

02:07:01.080 --> 02:07:02.873
We've got video on Ellie.
Five-by-five.

02:07:03.082 --> 02:07:04.958
STEVE:
She's through! She is in the net.

02:07:05.126 --> 02:07:08.128
She's alive. Get the White House.
Get the president on the phone.

02:07:08.296 --> 02:07:10.672
What's going on, Steve? How is she?
How is she?

02:07:10.840 --> 02:07:12.549
STEVE:
Ellie, this is Control. Do you copy?

02:07:12.717 --> 02:07:14.760
KENT: What's going on?
- I don't know. Hang on.

02:07:14.927 --> 02:07:16.553
- She is alive.
STEVE: Put her on the PA.

02:07:16.721 --> 02:07:18.305
Ellie, just hold on tight.

02:07:18.931 --> 02:07:22.225
We're still trying to determine
the nature of the malfunction...

02:07:22.393 --> 02:07:24.895
...but the important thing is you're okay.

02:07:25.063 --> 02:07:26.229
What?

02:07:26.397 --> 02:07:30.192
It's all right, Ellie.
The important thing is that you're safe.

02:07:31.152 --> 02:07:33.445
What malfunction?

02:07:34.781 --> 02:07:36.239
What...?

02:07:37.408 --> 02:07:39.034
What happened?

02:07:40.370 --> 02:07:42.037
What day is this?

02:07:42.705 --> 02:07:45.707
I'm sorry, Ellie,
did you say what day?

02:07:46.793 --> 02:07:49.044
How long was I gone?

02:07:50.797 --> 02:07:55.592
Ellie, the IPV dropped
straight through the Machine.

02:07:55.760 --> 02:07:57.427
You didn't go anywhere.

02:07:58.304 --> 02:08:01.640
But I did. I did go.

02:08:01.808 --> 02:08:04.184
That's what I've been trying
to tell everyone.

02:08:08.648 --> 02:08:11.733
But the headset
didn't record a single image?

02:08:11.901 --> 02:08:14.528
Just this. Static.

02:08:14.737 --> 02:08:15.779
Thank you.

02:08:15.947 --> 02:08:19.365
Now, doctor, let me show you
what we saw.

02:08:28.834 --> 02:08:32.670
Forty-three separate remote cameras
show exactly the same event.

02:08:32.838 --> 02:08:34.380
The IPV dropped straight through.

02:08:34.548 --> 02:08:38.134
Everyone who watched
saw exactly the same thing.

02:08:38.301 --> 02:08:40.136
Nothing happened.

02:08:41.471 --> 02:08:43.764
How do you explain this, doctor?

02:08:45.767 --> 02:08:46.892
I can't.

02:08:47.102 --> 02:08:48.561
CLINTON:
I would encourage you...

02:08:50.355 --> 02:08:54.525
...not to inflame this situation
beyond the facts.

02:08:54.693 --> 02:08:58.112
Let us deal with this on the facts.

02:08:58.280 --> 02:09:01.157
We are monitoring
what has actually happened.

02:09:01.324 --> 02:09:06.662
We are taking what we believe
is factually appropriate steps.

02:09:06.830 --> 02:09:10.040
Amid a flurry of accusations
and counter-accusations...

02:09:10.250 --> 02:09:12.835
...by the nations representing
the Machine Consortium...

02:09:13.003 --> 02:09:15.921
...the president has ordered
a special inquiry.

02:09:16.131 --> 02:09:18.924
However, the appointment
to the committee of Michael Kitz...

02:09:19.134 --> 02:09:21.969
...who has recently resigned
as National Security Advisor...

02:09:22.137 --> 02:09:24.472
...has raised a number of eyebrows
on Capitol Hill.

02:09:24.639 --> 02:09:28.434
I have made no decision to run for
Congress, I have announced no candidacy.

02:09:28.602 --> 02:09:31.187
The fact that I resigned
as National Security Advisor...

02:09:31.354 --> 02:09:33.063
...has nothing to do with anything...

02:09:33.231 --> 02:09:36.400
...other than I want to devote
all of my energy to this inquiry.

02:09:37.152 --> 02:09:41.821
The people of the world have a right
to know what really happened.

02:09:42.656 --> 02:09:45.158
And yet every scientific
instrument confirms...

02:09:45.326 --> 02:09:49.496
...the IPV was out of contact
for only a fraction of a second.

02:09:49.663 --> 02:09:51.706
Isn't that correct, doctor?

02:09:53.417 --> 02:09:55.710
A fraction of a second Earth time, yes.

02:09:56.587 --> 02:09:57.837
SENATOR:
Earth time?

02:09:58.005 --> 02:10:01.633
ELLIE: Senator, I believe that the Machine
opened up a wormhole...

02:10:01.801 --> 02:10:06.763
...a tunnel through the fabric of space-time,
also known as an Einstein-Rosen Bridge.

02:10:06.931 --> 02:10:11.059
Now, because of the effects of general
relativity, what I experienced as 18 hours...

02:10:11.227 --> 02:10:13.478
...passed instantaneously on Earth.

02:10:13.646 --> 02:10:17.982
Isn't it true that these wormholes you
speak of are merely theoretical predictions?

02:10:18.150 --> 02:10:20.902
There is no evidence
they actually exist, is there?

02:10:21.070 --> 02:10:22.779
ELLIE:
There is no direct evidence, no.

02:10:22.947 --> 02:10:24.697
KITZ:
Tell me something, doctor...

02:10:24.865 --> 02:10:27.992
...why do you think these aliens
would go to all this trouble?

02:10:28.160 --> 02:10:32.372
Bring you tens of thousands of light years
and then send you home without proof?

02:10:33.040 --> 02:10:35.750
They said that's how it's been done
for billions of years.

02:10:36.126 --> 02:10:39.712
KITZ: That's very neat. You have no proof
because they didn't want you to have any.

02:10:39.880 --> 02:10:44.634
A phenomenon known in psychiatric circles,
I believe, as a self-reinforcing delusion.

02:10:45.219 --> 02:10:46.845
Is that what you think? Delusional?

02:10:47.012 --> 02:10:51.140
KITZ: Well, I do think you may have suffered
some kind of an episode. Yeah, I do.

02:10:51.308 --> 02:10:54.185
Doctor, I'd like to propose
an alternate hypothesis...

02:10:54.395 --> 02:10:58.064
...and I'd like you to bring
your scientific expertise to bear on it.

02:10:58.232 --> 02:11:01.442
To fake a signal from Vega...

02:11:02.111 --> 02:11:03.695
...what would you need?

02:11:05.405 --> 02:11:09.199
You would need a satellite to transmit
the signal, but it would be impossible to...

02:11:09.367 --> 02:11:13.287
You'd need a satellite and need launch
capabilities to put the satellite into orbit.

02:11:13.454 --> 02:11:16.665
And the message itself.
To put something like this together...

02:11:16.833 --> 02:11:19.126
...so complex,
drawing on many disciplines...

02:11:19.294 --> 02:11:21.253
- Would be impossible.
KITZ: Impossible?

02:11:22.547 --> 02:11:24.464
Impossible?

02:11:24.632 --> 02:11:28.260
Is there anyone who might
have been up to the challenge?

02:11:28.428 --> 02:11:30.888
Someone with extraordinary
technical expertise...

02:11:31.055 --> 02:11:33.265
...enormous financial resources...

02:11:33.433 --> 02:11:37.811
...someone perverse enough,
eccentric enough to come up with the idea?

02:11:39.188 --> 02:11:40.230
Hadden?

02:11:41.190 --> 02:11:43.650
S. R. Hadden.

02:11:43.818 --> 02:11:46.445
[CROWD MURMURING]

02:11:47.947 --> 02:11:50.991
You're implying that this was
all some kind of a hoax?

02:11:51.159 --> 02:11:52.409
That he engineered this?

02:11:52.577 --> 02:11:53.827
KITZ:
S. R. Hadden...

02:11:53.995 --> 02:11:58.874
...a legendary power broker and manipulator
in perhaps his final bid for immortality.

02:11:59.042 --> 02:12:01.710
Maybe he wanted to explore
and exploit new technologies...

02:12:01.878 --> 02:12:04.087
...and get the governments
to pick up the tab.

02:12:04.297 --> 02:12:07.049
Perhaps this was his
final altruistic gesture...

02:12:07.300 --> 02:12:11.011
...to unite the world in some common goal.
Maybe all of the above.

02:12:11.179 --> 02:12:16.099
S. R. Hadden, a brilliant
and complicated man.

02:12:18.645 --> 02:12:22.898
Doctor, are you familiar
with the scientific precept...

02:12:23.066 --> 02:12:25.192
...known as Occam's razor?

02:12:31.406 --> 02:12:32.573
ELLIE:
Yes.

02:12:34.576 --> 02:12:36.661
It means that all things being equal...

02:12:36.828 --> 02:12:39.330
...the simplest explanation
tends to be the right one.

02:12:39.498 --> 02:12:41.040
KITZ:
Exactly.

02:12:41.208 --> 02:12:43.668
Now, you tell me.
What is more likely here?

02:12:43.835 --> 02:12:47.296
That a message from aliens
results in a magical machine...

02:12:47.464 --> 02:12:50.174
...that whisks you away
to the center of the galaxy...

02:12:50.384 --> 02:12:53.260
...to go windsurfing with your dad
and a split second later...

02:12:53.428 --> 02:12:56.889
...returns you home
without a single shred of proof?

02:12:57.057 --> 02:13:00.851
Or that your experience
is the result of being...

02:13:01.019 --> 02:13:05.481
...the unwitting star in the farewell
performance of one S.R. Hadden?

02:13:05.649 --> 02:13:09.443
A man with the means, motive and
opportunity to play you and the rest of us...

02:13:09.695 --> 02:13:13.906
...as pawns in the biggest, most elaborate,
most expensive hoax of all time?

02:13:15.200 --> 02:13:17.118
MAN:
Dr. Arroway.

02:13:18.996 --> 02:13:23.374
You come to us with no evidence,
no record...

02:13:23.542 --> 02:13:25.334
...no artifacts.

02:13:25.502 --> 02:13:29.672
Only a story that, to put it mildly,
strains credibility.

02:13:30.799 --> 02:13:33.926
Over half a trillion dollars were spent.

02:13:34.094 --> 02:13:37.096
Dozens of lives were lost.

02:13:37.723 --> 02:13:42.435
Are you really gonna sit there
and tell us we should just take this all...

02:13:43.186 --> 02:13:44.729
...on faith?

02:13:48.734 --> 02:13:50.943
KITZ:
Please answer the question, doctor.

02:13:54.864 --> 02:13:56.948
Is it possible that it didn't happen?

02:13:57.116 --> 02:13:58.283
Yes.

02:13:58.451 --> 02:14:00.994
[CROWD MURMURING]

02:14:01.162 --> 02:14:04.289
As a scientist I must concede that.
I must volunteer that.

02:14:08.627 --> 02:14:10.545
KITZ:
Wait a minute, let me get this straight.

02:14:10.713 --> 02:14:14.591
You admit you have absolutely no
physical evidence to back up your story?

02:14:14.925 --> 02:14:15.967
Yes.

02:14:16.135 --> 02:14:19.179
You admit that you very well may have
hallucinated this whole thing?

02:14:19.346 --> 02:14:22.140
- Yes.
- You admit that if you were in our position...

02:14:22.308 --> 02:14:26.061
...you would respond with exactly the same
degree of incredulity and skepticism?

02:14:26.228 --> 02:14:27.479
Yes.

02:14:27.646 --> 02:14:30.607
Then why don't you simply withdraw
your testimony and concede...

02:14:30.775 --> 02:14:35.945
...that this journey to the center of
the galaxy in fact never took place?

02:14:38.949 --> 02:14:40.950
Because I can't.

02:14:41.118 --> 02:14:43.828
[CROWD MURMURING]

02:14:47.500 --> 02:14:51.169
I had an experience.

02:14:52.838 --> 02:14:55.423
I can't prove it. I can't even explain it.

02:14:55.591 --> 02:14:58.676
But everything that I know as
a human being, everything I am...

02:14:58.844 --> 02:15:00.970
...tells me it was real.

02:15:03.015 --> 02:15:06.893
I was given something wonderful,
something that changed me forever.

02:15:07.061 --> 02:15:08.603
A vision...

02:15:08.771 --> 02:15:10.855
...of the universe...

02:15:11.023 --> 02:15:13.691
...that tells us undeniably...

02:15:13.859 --> 02:15:16.110
...how tiny and insignificant...

02:15:16.277 --> 02:15:19.988
...and how rare and precious we all are.

02:15:21.157 --> 02:15:23.575
A vision that tells us
that we belong to something...

02:15:23.743 --> 02:15:29.414
...that is greater than ourselves,
that we are not... That none of us are alone.

02:15:34.045 --> 02:15:38.048
I wish I could share that.

02:15:40.552 --> 02:15:41.718
I wish...

02:15:43.179 --> 02:15:47.224
...that everyone,
if even for one moment...

02:15:47.392 --> 02:15:53.147
...could feel that awe
and humility and hope.

02:15:53.565 --> 02:15:55.566
But...

02:16:01.739 --> 02:16:04.032
That continues to be my wish.

02:16:45.199 --> 02:16:48.534
MAN 1: Dr. Arroway, get a picture, please?
Get a photo over here?

02:16:50.162 --> 02:16:51.787
WOMAN:
Here comes Ellie.

02:17:28.075 --> 02:17:30.993
MAN 2:
Reverend Joss! Reverend Joss!

02:17:31.161 --> 02:17:34.538
MAN 3: Reverend Joss, what do you
believe? What do you believe?

02:17:38.794 --> 02:17:42.797
As a person of faith, I'm bound by
a different covenant than Dr. Arroway.

02:17:44.549 --> 02:17:46.800
But our goal is one and the same.

02:17:47.302 --> 02:17:48.928
The pursuit of truth.

02:17:52.474 --> 02:17:53.766
I, for one, believe her.

02:18:17.331 --> 02:18:20.208
So, what happens now?
We give her a medal?

02:18:20.376 --> 02:18:23.253
I'd say at least a healthy grant.

02:18:23.421 --> 02:18:26.880
I assume you read the confidential report
from the investigating committee?

02:18:27.091 --> 02:18:28.842
KITZ:
I flipped through it.

02:18:29.010 --> 02:18:33.221
I was especially interested
in the section on Arroway's video unit.

02:18:34.014 --> 02:18:36.349
The one that recorded the static.

02:18:37.601 --> 02:18:39.311
Continue.

02:18:39.937 --> 02:18:43.772
The fact that it recorded static
isn't what interests me.

02:18:48.611 --> 02:18:49.987
Continue.

02:18:50.865 --> 02:18:52.699
What interests me...

02:18:52.867 --> 02:18:56.702
...is that it recorded
approximately 18 hours of it.

02:19:01.959 --> 02:19:03.877
That is interesting, isn't it?

02:19:10.550 --> 02:19:14.387
ELLIE: You can see over there,
we're building 45 brand-new dishes.

02:19:14.555 --> 02:19:18.516
And that means when you put them
together with all the radio telescopes...

02:19:18.683 --> 02:19:20.184
...all over the world...

02:19:20.352 --> 02:19:25.022
...then we get to hear farther into space
than anybody has ever heard before.

02:19:25.191 --> 02:19:26.231
Yeah.

02:19:26.398 --> 02:19:29.234
Are there other people
out there in the universe?

02:19:30.278 --> 02:19:33.030
That's a good question.
What do you think, huh?

02:19:33.615 --> 02:19:36.950
- I don't know.
- That's a good answer.

02:19:37.826 --> 02:19:38.869
Skeptic, huh?

02:19:40.163 --> 02:19:45.041
The important thing is that you all
keep searching for your own answers.

02:19:45.209 --> 02:19:48.045
I'll tell you one thing
about the universe, though.

02:19:48.213 --> 02:19:52.091
The universe is a pretty big place.

02:19:53.093 --> 02:19:58.597
It's bigger than anything
anyone has ever dreamed of before.

02:20:00.183 --> 02:20:01.850
So if it's just us...

02:20:03.478 --> 02:20:06.271
...it seems like an awful waste of space.

02:20:07.774 --> 02:20:09.149
Right?

